igail%20Spanberger%20of%20Virginia%3Cp%3ERichard%20Vogel%20and%20Nathan%20Howard%2FAP%20Photo%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ERep.%20Katie%20Porter%20told%20off%20a%20fellow%20House%20Democrat%20after%20a%20contentious%20vote.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EAccording%20to%20a%20new%20book%2C%20Porter%20told%20Rep.%20Abigail%20Spanberger%20to%C2%A0%26quot%3Bgo%20be%20a%20Republican%26quot%3B%20after%20she%20complained%20about%20Democratic%20amendments.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ETensions%20were%20high%20on%20the%20floor%20in%202019%20as%20a%20border%20package%20divided%20House%20Democrats.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ERep.%20Katie%20Porter%20of%20California%20clashed%20with%20a%20fellow%20House%20Democrat%20on%20the%20House%20floor%20as%20tensions%20flared%20in%202019%20over%20a%20contentious%20border-related%20bill%20that%20ended%20up%20splitting%20the%20party.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20journalist%20Ryan%20Grim's%20new%20book%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%3FamazonTrackingID%3Dbiauto-64986-20%26h%3D5f08ab7ab3230a510e79db73d94723284bc721115be72ac9b03a772293659752%26postID%3D6577659a4c878294df235088%26postSlug%3Dkatie-porter-abigail-spanberger-go-be-a-republican-border-democrats-2023-12%26site%3Dbi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.amazon.com%252FSquad-AOC-Hope-Political-Revolution%252Fdp%252F1250869072%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Squad%3A%20AOC%20and%20the%20Hope%20of%20a%20Political%20Revolution%3Cem%3E%26quot%3B%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Porter%20lashed%20out%20at%20Rep.%20Abigail%20Spanberger%2C%20a%20Virginia%20Democrat%2C%20after%20she%20overheard%20Spanberger%20complain%20about%20more%20progressive%20Democrats%20trying%20to%20amend%20a%20%244.6%20billion%20border%20aid%20package%20that%20already%20passed%20the%20Senate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAbigail%20Spanberger%2C%20a%20former%20CIA%20official%20turned%20moderate%20Democrat%2C%20waved%20the%20House%20amendments%20around%2C%20saying%20she%20was%20tired%20of%20being%20forced%20to%20vote%20against%20her%20values%2C%26quot%3B%20Grim%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGrim%20wrote%20that%20Porter%20was%20%26quot%3Bstunned.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3B'What%20values%3F'%20Porter%20said%2C%20per%20Grim.%20'Go%20be%20a%20Republican%2C%20then.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20separate%20statements%20to%20Business%20Insider%2C%20spokespersons%20for%20both%20Spanberger%20and%20Porter%20said%20the%20pair%20were%20still%20friends.%20Both%20lawmakers%20voted%20in%20favor%20of%20the%20bill.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSince%20they%20were%20sworn%20in%2C%20Reps.%20Porter%20and%20Spanberger%20have%20enjoyed%20a%20strong%20friendship%20and%20working%20relationship%20that%20continues%20today.%20Both%20representing%20ideologically%20diverse%20districts%2C%20they%20find%20common%20ground%20in%20their%20commitment%20to%20democracy%2C%20willingness%20to%20debate%20ideas%2C%20and%20respect%20for%20Americans'%20many%20viewpoints%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20spokesperson%20for%20Porter%20said%20in%20a%20statement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20spokesperson%20for%20Spanberger%20added%2C%20%26quot%3BRep.%20Spanberger%20and%20Rep.%20Porter%20remain%20friends%20and%20have%20engaged%20in%20many%20policy%20conversations%20during%20their%20time%20in%20Congress.%20The%20U.S.%20Senate%20voted%2084%20to%208%20to%20pass%20this%20funding%20bill%2C%20and%20more%20than%20300%20Members%20of%20the%20U.S.%20House%20%E2%80%94%20including%20both%20Rep.%20Spanberger%20and%20Rep.%20Porter%20%E2%80%94%20supported%20passing%20this%20emergency%20legislation.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20Democrats%2C%20including%20then-House%20Speaker%20Nancy%20Pelosi%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.texastribune.org%2F2019%2F06%2F27%2Fborder-aid-migrants-passed-house-senate-bills-are-different%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewanted%20to%20amend%20the%20proposal%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20requiring%20the%20Trump%20administration%20to%20only%20use%20some%20of%20the%20new%20money%20for%20specific%20supplies%20such%20as%20food%2C%20water%2C%20and%20blankets.%20Instead%2C%20more%20centrist%20lawmakers%2C%20including%20Spanberger%2C%20called%20on%20Congress%20to%20pass%20the%20bill%20as%20it%20stood%20without%20risking%20the%20possibility%20of%20lawmakers%20leaving%20town%20for%20their%20July%204%20recess%20without%20doing%20nothing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThose%20centrists%20and%20many%20other%20Democrats%20held%20firm%20and%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2019%2F06%2F27%2Fus%2Fpolitics%2Fborder-funding-immigration.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20forced%20Pelosi%20to%20back%20down%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20bill%2C%20which%20passed%20the%20Senate%2084%20to%208%2C%20passed%20the%20House%20305%20to%20102.%20But%20despite%20holding%20the%20majority%2C%20the%20legislation%20passed%20with%20far%20more%20Republican%20votes%20than%20Democrats.%20Ninety-five%20House%20Democrats%20voted%20against%20the%20legislation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20opponents'%20vented%20their%20raw%20emotions%20after%20the%20defeat.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSince%20when%20did%20the%20Problem%20Solvers%20Caucus%20become%20the%20Child%20Abuse%20Caucus%3F%26quot%3B%20Rep.%20Mark%20Pocan%2C%20a%20Wisconsin%20Democrat%2C%20who%20at%20the%20time%20was%20leading%20the%20Congressional%20Progressive%20Caucus%2C%20wrote%20on%20Twitter%20of%20the%20bipartisan%20group%20of%20centrist%20lawmakers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESpanberger%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fbi.slack.com%2Farchives%2FD01K6EFTU11%2Fp1702324627702219%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elater%20told%20The%20Washington%20Post%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20episode%20taught%20her%20%26quot%3Bthat%20for%20some%20people%20ideology%20matters%20more%20than%20putting%20food%20in%20the%20mouth%20of%20a%20child.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBoth%20congresswomen%20will%20soon%20to%20be%20leaving%20the%20House.%20Porter%20is%20currently%20running%20to%20replace%20the%20late%20Dianne%20Feinstein%20in%20the%20Senate.%20Spanberger%20has%20said%20she%20will%20leave%20the%20chamber%20so%20she%20can%20run%20for%20governor%20of%20Virginia.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fkatie-porter-abigail-spanberger-go-be-a-republican-border-democrats-2023-12%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702334465000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65778c0f0ec98e92f74e6042%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fkatie-porter-abigail-spanberger-go-be-a-republican-border-democrats-2023-12%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Porter%20told%20off%20fellow%20House%20Democrat%20Rep.%20Abigail%20Spanberger%20in%202019%20after%20a%20vote%20on%20a%20border%20package%20that%20divided%20the%20party.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22bgriffiths%40insider.com%20(Brent%20D.%20Griffiths)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A72%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fkatie-porter-abigail-spanberger-go-be-a-republican-border-democrats-2023-12%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Why%20Spotify%E2%80%99s%20New%20Payment%20Model%20Falls%20Short%20For%20Emerging%20Artists%3A%20Guest%20Column%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702333713000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F07%2FSpotify-Earnings.jpg%3Fw%3D1000%26h%3D563%26crop%3D1%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2F%3Fp%3D1235834319%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22After%20much%20speculation%20on%20what%20Spotify%E2%80%99s%20updated%20payment%20model%20would%20actually%20look%20like%2C%20the%20streaming%20giant%20finally%20released%20a%20comprehensive%20breakdown%20in%20a%20blog%20post%20late%20last%20month.%20Although%20the%20post%20was%20titled%20Modernizing%20Our%20Royalty%20System%20to%20Drive%20an%20Additional%20%241%20Billion%20toward%20Emerging%20and%20Professional%20Artists%2C%20emerging%20artists%20have%20been%20co