C%22%3Einterview%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20Monday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EExxon%20Mobil%20and%20Chevron%20have%20both%20been%20expanding%20their%20footprints%20in%20the%20region.%20Exxon%20began%20production%20at%20its%20third%20project%20in%20Payara%2C%20Guyana%2C%20this%20year%2C%20bringing%20its%20total%20production%20capacity%20in%20the%20region%20to%20approximately%20620%2C000%20barrels%20per%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20in%20October%2C%20Chevron%20signed%20a%20deal%20to%20acquire%20oil%20company%20Hess%2C%20with%20one%20big%20trophy%20of%20the%20agreement%20being%20a%20project%20off%20the%20coast%20of%20Guyana.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20long-simmering%20antagonisms%20between%20Guyana%20and%20its%20neighbor%20Venezuela%20have%20resurfaced%20recently%2C%20with%20Venezuela%20claiming%20a%20big%20chunk%20of%20Guyana's%20land.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSo%20far%20it's%20more%20bluster%2C%26quot%3B%20Yergin%20said.%20%26quot%3BNicol%C3%A1s%20Maduro%2C%20the%20dictator%20president%20of%20Venezuela%2C%20had%20this%20farcical%20referendum%20where%20maybe%2010%25%20of%20people%20voted%20claiming%20two%20thirds%20of%20Guyana.%20But%20what's%20really%20piqued%20his%20interest%20is%20offshore%20oil.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20flare-up%20should%20be%20taken%20seriously%20in%20the%20US%2C%20Yergin%20warned%2C%20as%20Maduro%20remains%20in%20a%20weak%20position%20with%20the%20country%20seeing%20a%20large%20refugee%20crisis.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20after%20years%20of%20economic%20collapse%20have%20sent%20millions%20of%20Venezuelans%20fleeing%20the%20country%2C%20landing%20mostly%20in%20other%20part%20of%20Latin%20America.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20risk%20is%20that%20he%20might%20do%20something%2C%20he%20might%20seize%20a%20piece%20of%20territory%2C%20plant%20a%20flag%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20of%20course%2C%20you%20have%20to%20keep%20in%20mind%20that%20Maduro's%20close%20allies%20are%20Russia%2C%20Cuba%2C%20and%20increasingly%2C%20Iran.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3