ns%20in%20the%20CBI's%20powers%20to%20investigate%20crucial%20cases%2C%20a%20Parliamentary%20panel%20on%20Monday%20said%20there%20was%20a%20dire%20need%20to%20enact%20a%20new%20law%20and%20give%20wider%20powers%20to%20the%20federal%20agency%20so%20that%20it%20can%20probe%20cases%20without%20a%20%26quot%3Bstate's%20consent%20and%20interference%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20same%20time%2C%20the%20panel%20said%20that%20some%20safeguards%20should%20also%20be%20laid%20down%20to%20ensure%20objectivity%20and%20impartiality%20in%20the%20functioning%20of%20CBI%20so%20that%20the%20states%20also%20don't%20feel%20discriminated%20against.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20per%20the%20provisions%20of%20the%20Delhi%20Special%20Police%20Establishment%20(DSPE)%20Act%2C%20which%20governs%20the%20functioning%20of%20the%20CBI%2C%20the%20consent%20of%20the%20state%20government%20is%20a%20pre-requisite%20for%20any%20investigation%20by%20the%20Central%20Bureau%20of%20Investigation%20(CBI).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENine%20states%20have%20withdrawn%20the%20general%20consent%20to%20the%20CBI%20for%20investigating%20cases%2C%20according%20to%20a%20report%20tabled%20by%20the%20panel%20in%20Parliament%20on%20Monday.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EState%20governments%20have%20granted%20general%20consent%20to%20the%20CBI%20for%20investigation%20in%20a%20%26quot%3Bspecified%20class%20of%20offences%20against%20specified%20categories%20of%20persons%26quot%3B%2C%20according%20to%20the%20provision%20of%20Section%206%20of%20the%20DSPE%20Act.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20investigation%20of%20any%20matter%20in%20such%20state%2C%20which%20is%20not%20covered%20in%20the%20aforesaid%20consent%2C%20specific%20consent%20of%20the%20state%20government%20is%20required%20for%20the%20CBI%20to%20investigate%20in%20the%20state%20and%20the%20agency%20seeks%20such%20consent%20on%20a%20case-by-case%20basis.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWith%20reference%20to%20this%20only%20the%20Committee%20reiterates%20that%20as%20on%20date%2C%20nine%20states%20have%20withdrawn%20the%20general%20consent%20they%20had%20given%20to%20the%20CBI%20for%20investigating%20cases.%20This%20has%20led%20to%20severe%20limitations%20on%20the%20powers%20of%20CBI%20to%20investigate%20crucial%20cases%20impartially%20and%20objectively%20which%20will%20give%20rise%20to%20corruption%20and%20organised%20crimes%20in%20states%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHence%2C%20as%20recommended%20earlier%2C%20apart%20from%20the%20DSPE%20Act%2C%201946%2C%20there%20is%20a%20dire%20need%20to%20enact%20a%20new%20law%20and%20define%20the%20status%20and%20functions%20and%20give%20wider%20powers%20to%20CBI%20to%20investigate%20such%20crucial%20cases%20without%20the%20need%20for%20a%20state's%20consent%20and%20interference%2C%20the%20panel%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20panel's%20report%20comes%20in%20the%20back%20of%20non-NDA%20governments%20in%20some%20states%20withdrawing%20general%20consent%20to%20the%20CBI%20while%20accusing%20the%20Centre%20of%20misusing%20agencies%20to%20target%20political%20rivals.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAt%20the%20same%20time%2C%20in%20the%20same%20Act%2C%20some%20safeguards%20should%20also%20be%20laid%20down%20to%20ensure%20objectivity%20and%20impartiality%20in%20the%20functioning%20of%20CBI%20so%20that%20the%20states%20also%20don't%20feel%20discriminated%20and%20absolutely%20powerless%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20panel%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%98State's%20consent%20clause'%20should%20be%20removed%20only%20in%20such%20cases%20that%20are%20considered%20to%20be%20a%20threat%20to%20the%20nation's%20security%20and%20integrity%20and%20any%20delay%20in%20investigation%20of%20such%20cases%20by%20the%20CBI%20may%20lead%20to%20a%20general%20dissatisfaction%20among%20the%20citizens%20of%20the%20country%2C%20said%20the%20135th%20report%20of%20the%20Department%20related%20Parliamentary%20Standing%20Committee%20on%20Personnel%2C%20Public%20Grievances%2C%20Law%20and%20Justice.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20CBI%20has%20recently%20proposed%20suitable%20amendments%20in%20recruitment%20rules%20for%20its%20various%20posts%20including%20that%20of%20inspector%2C%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccordingly%2C%20the%20federal%20agency%20has%20proposed%20that%2060%20per%20cent%20of%20posts%20of%20inspectors%20are%20to%20be%20filled%20by%20%26quot%3Bpromotion%26quot%3B%20and%2040%20per%20cent%20on%20a%20%26quot%3Bdeputation%2Fabsorption%26quot%3B%20basis%2C%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20existing%20mode%20of%20recruitment%20follows%20the%20%26quot%3B50%3A50%26quot%3B%20formula%20for%20filling%20up%20these%20posts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20aforesaid%20proposal%20is%20already%20under%20consideration.%20However%2C%20the%20position%20will%20be%20reviewed%20in%20case%20the%20proposed%20amendment%20does%20not%20meet%20out%20the%20functional%20requirement%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20panel%20was%20informed%20that%20as%20many%20as%20308%20posts%20(including%20that%20of%20a%20joint%20director%2C%20deputy%20inspector%20general%2C%20superintendent%20of%20police%2C%20etc.)%20in%20the%20CBI%20were%20filled%20last%20year%20alone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702321020000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2022-08%2Frloqk36c_cbi-generic-650_625x300_19_August_22.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fneed-law-for-cbi-to-probe-cases-without-state-consent-parliamentary-panel-4653481%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20Parliamentary%20panel%20on%20Monday%20said%20there%20was%20a%20dire%20need%20to%20enact%20a%20new%20law%20and%20give%20wider%20powers%20to%20the%20federal%20agency%20so%20that%20it%20can%20probe%20cases%20without%20a%20%26quot%3Bstate's%20consent%20and%20interference%26quot%3B.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%