ny%3A%20Russian%20opposition%20leader%20'removed%20from%20penal%20colony'%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702311480000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fichef.bbci.co.uk%2Fnews%2F1024%2Fbranded_news%2F12120%2Fproduction%2F_130661047_alexei_navalny_4_epa.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-europe-67680342%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Alexei%20Navalny's%20associates%20say%20they%20don't%20know%20where%20he%20is%2C%20after%20six%20days%20of%20uncertainty.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A226%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-europe-67680342%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-bbc-co-uk.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-europe-67680342.amp%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-europe-67680342.amp%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Citing%20SC's%20Silence%20on%20J%26amp%3BK's%20Statehood%2C%20Opposition%20Parties%20Raise%20Concerns%20Over%20Federalism%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F11214319%2FEffect-24.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EN%3C%2Fb%3E%3Cstrong%3Eew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Opposition%20parties%20have%20raised%20questions%20about%20the%20future%20of%20federalism%20in%20the%20country%20after%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20in%20its%20verdict%20on%20Monday%2C%20December%2011%2C%20upheld%20the%20abrogation%20of%20Article%20370%20through%20the%20constitutional%20order%20that%20read%20down%20the%20Article%20in%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20delivered%20its%20verdict%20after%20hearing%20the%20petitions%20challenging%20the%20Narendra%20Modi%20government%E2%80%99s%20move%20to%20bifurcate%20the%20erstwhile%20state%20of%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20state%20into%20two%20Union%20territories%20in%20August%202019%20through%20the%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20Reorganisation%20Act%202019.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20a%20press%20conference%20in%20the%20national%20capital%20on%20Monday%20evening%20the%20Congress%20party%20said%20that%20it%20%E2%80%9Crespectfully%20disagreed%E2%80%9D%20with%20the%20apex%20court%E2%80%99s%20order.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CPrima%20facie%2C%20we%20respectfully%20disagree%20with%20the%20judgement%20on%20the%20manner%20in%20which%20Article%20370%20was%20abrogated%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20former%20Union%20home%20minister%20P.%20Chidambaram%20at%20the%20press%20conference.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20reiterate%20the%20CWC%20(Congress%20Working%20Committee)%20resolution%20in%20August%202019%20that%20Article%20370%20deserved%20to%20be%20honoured%20until%20it%20was%20amended%20strictly%20in%20accordance%20with%20the%20constitution%20of%20India.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20party%20also%20said%20that%20it%20is%20%E2%80%9Cdisappointed%E2%80%9D%20that%20the%20court%20did%20not%20decide%20on%20the%20question%20of%20whether%20the%20parliament%20can%20convert%20a%20state%20into%20a%20Union%20territory.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20validity%20of%20the%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20Reorganisation%20Act%202019%20was%20one%20of%20the%20issues%20before%20the%20court%2C%20it%20did%20not%20rule%20on%20it%20in%20view%20of%20the%20submission%20by%20the%20solicitor%20general%20of%20India%20that%20the%20statehood%20of%20J%26amp%3BK%20will%20be%20restored%20as%20soon%20as%20possible%2C%20reported%20%3Cem%3ELiveLaw.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%2C%20however%2C%20upheld%20the%20creation%20of%20the%20Union%20territory%20of%20Ladakh%20citing%20Article%203%20of%20the%20constitution%20that%20allows%20a%20portion%20of%20a%20state%20to%20be%20made%20into%20a%20union%20territory.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%E2%80%99re%20also%20disappointed%20that%20the%20honourable%20Supreme%20Court%20did%20not%20decide%20the%20question%20of%20dismembering%20the%20state%20and%20reducing%20its%20status%20to%20two%20Union%20territories%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Chidambaram.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERajya%20Sabha%20MP%20and%20lawyer%20Abhishek%20Manu%20Singhvi%20who%20was%20also%20present%20at%20the%20press%20conference%20said%20that%20under%20Article%203%20the%20whole%20state%20cannot%20be%20made%20into%20a%20Union%20territory.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThere%20is%20a%20strange%20contradiction%20in%20this%20judgement%20about%20the%20issue%20of%20statehood%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CUnder%20Article%203%20of%20the%20constitution%2C%20you%20can%20make%20a%20part%20of%20a%20state%20a%20union%20territory%2C%20or%20divide%20a%20state%20into%20two%20or%20three%20states.%20But%20there%20is%20a%20condition%20in%20Article%203%20that%20some%20part%20of%20it%20should%20remain%20a%20state.%20You%20cannot%20make%20the%20whole%20state%20just%20a%20union%20territory.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20contradiction%20in%20this%20decision%20is%20that%20you%20have%20divided%20an%20entire%20state%20into%20two%20Union%20territories.%20And%20about%20one%20Union%20territory%20you%20have%20said%20that%20we%20are%20not%20deciding%20on%20the%20validity%20because%20we%20have%20been%20assured%20that%20full%20statehood%20will%20be%20restored%20as%20soon%20as%20possible.%20In%20the%20case%20of%20the%20other%20Union%20territory%2C%20it%20has%20been%20held%20that%20it%20is%20valid.%C2%A0%20So%20until%20a%20part%20of%20this%20whole%20territory%20is%20not%20a%20state%2C%20till%20then%20this%20cannot%20be%20valid%20under%20Article%203.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThis%20is%20showing%20a%20big%20contradiction%20in%20this%20decision%20and%20a%20constitutional%20error%20in%20this%20judgement%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOther%20opposition%20parties%20have%20also%20questioned%20the%20court%E2%80%99s%20refusal%20to%20rule%20on%20the%20validity%20of%20stripping%20the%20erstwhile%20state%20into%20two%20Union%20territories.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20CPI(M)%2C%20also%20a%20petitioner%20in%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20in%20the%20matter%2C%20issued%20a%20statement%20saying%20that%20the%20judgement%20is%20%E2%80%9Cdisturbing%20and%20has%20serious%20consequences%20for%20the%20federal%20structure%20of%20our%20Constitution%20which%20is%20one%20of%20its%20fundamental%20features.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20statement%20of%20the%20party%E2%80%99s%20politburo%20expressed%20concerns%20that%20the%20verdict%20allows%20the%20Union%20government%20to%20unilaterally%20%E2%80%9Cinitiate%20the%20formation%20of%20new%20states%2C%20alteration%20of%20areas%2C%20boundaries%20or%20names%20of%20existing%20states.%20This%20may%20well%20lead%20to%20a%20serious%20undermining%20of%20federalism%20and%20the%20rights%20of%20the%20elected%20state%20legislatures%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20said%20that%20the%20verdict%20%E2%80%9Chas%20serious%20implications%20for%20the%20federal%20structure%20of%20our%20constitution%20and%20is%20inclined%20to%20strengthen%20a%20Unitary%20state%20structure%20in%20the%20name%20of%20%E2%80%98integration%E2%80%99%20and%20by%20invoking%20%E2%80%98national%20security%E2%80%99.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAIMIM%20MP%20Asaduddin%20Owaisi%20said%20that%20the%20%E2%80%9Cdowngrading%20of%20the%20state%20to%20Union%20territory%20is%20a%20grand%20betrayal%E2%80%9D%20to%20the%20people%20of%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20and%20this%20will%20not%20stop%20the%20Union%20government%20from%20making%20other%20states%20into%20union%20territories.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CLet%20us%20be%20clear%20that%2C%20in%20Bommai%20judgement%2C%20SC%20had%20said%20that%20federalism%20is%20part%20of%20the%20basic%20structure%20of%20the%20constitution.%20Federalism%20means%20that%20the%20state%20has%20its%20voice%20and%20in%20its%20area%20of%20competence%2C%20it%20has%20complete%20freedom%20to%20operate.%20How%20is%20it%20that%20Parliament%20can%20speak%20in%20place%20of%20the%20Assembly%3F%20How%20is%20it%20that%20Parliament%20can%20pass%20a%20resolution%20that%20was%20to%20be%20passed%20by%20the%20Assembly%20in%20the%20constitution%3F%20For%20me%2C%20the%20manner%20in%20which%20370%20was%20abrogated%20was%20a%20violation%20of%20constitutional%20morality.%20Even%20worse%2C%20the%20abrogation%2C%20bifurcation%20and%20downgrading%20of%20the%20state%20to%20union%20territory%20is%20a%20grand%20betrayal%20of%20the%20solemn%20promise%20that%20the%20Union%20of%20India%20had%20made%20to%20the%20people%20of%20Kashmir%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20wrote%20on%20X%20(formerly%20Twitter).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20data-width%3D%5C%22550%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%20data-dnt%3D%5C%22true%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fhashtag%2FArticle370%3Fsrc%3Dhash%26ref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3E%23Article370%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Cbr%3E1.%20In%202019%2C%20the%20CJI%20spoke%20at%20a%20seminar%20and%20said%20that%20%E2%80%9Cpublic%20deliberation%20will%20always%20be%20a%20threat%20to%20those%20who%20achieved%20power%20in%20its%20absence.%E2%80%9D%20The%20question%20is%20whether%20you%20can%20abrogate%20the%20special%20status%20of%20a%20state%20by%20putting%20the%20whole%20state%20in%20curfew%2C%20while%20it%20is%E2%80%A6%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%94%20Asaduddin%20Owaisi%20(%40asadowaisi)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fasadowaisi%2Fstatus%2F1734118032841011544%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3EDecember%2011%2C%202023%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20have%20said%20it%20once%20and%20I%20will%20say%20it%20again.%20Once%20this%20has%20been%20legitimised%2C%20there%20is%20nothing%20stopping%20the%20union%20govt%20from%20making%20Chennai%2C%20Kolkata%2C%20Hyderabad%20or%20Mumbai%20a%20Union%20Territory.%20Let%E2%80%99s%20look%20at%20the%20case%20of%20Ladakh%2C%20it%20is%20being%20ruled%20by%20Lt.%20Governor%2C%20with%20no%20democratic%20representation%20at%20all.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EParties%20like%20the%20Shiv%20Sena%20have%20welcomed%20the%20judgement%20but%20demanded%20that%20elections%20be%20held%20at%20the%20earliest.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESpeaking%20in%20the%20Rajya%20Sabha%20on%20the%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20Reservation%20(Amendment)%20Bill%2C%202023%2C%20Shiv%20Sena%20MP%20Priyanka%20Chaturvedi%20said%20that%20her%20party%20%E2%80%9Cwholeheartedly%20welcomes%E2%80%9D%20the%20apex%20court%E2%80%99s%20verdict%20and%20reminded%20Union%20home%20minister%20Amit%20Shah%20that%20while%20introducing%20the%20Bill%20in%202019%2C%20he%20had%20promised%20to%20restore%20peace%20and%20hold%20elections%20at%20the%20earliest.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20data-width%3D%5C%22550%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%20data-dnt%3D%5C%22true%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EWholeheartedly%20welcome%20the%20SC%20decision%20on%20Article%20370.%20Now%20I%20hope%20with%20this%20decision%2C%20we%20would%20have%20elections%20announced%20for%20J%26amp%3BK%20immediately%20and%20ensure%20that%20democratic%20rights%20and%20voices%20of%20the%20citizens%20are%20heard.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%94%20Priyanka%20Chaturvedi%F0%9F%87%AE%F0%9F%87%B3%20(%40priyankac19)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fpriyankac19%2Fstatus%2F1734117081539629110%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3EDecember%2011%2C%202023%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20post%20on%20X%2C%20she%20wrote%20that%20with%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20decision%20elections%20should%20be%20announced%20immediately%20%E2%80%9Cand%20ensure%20that%20democratic%20rights%20and%20voices%20of%20the%20citizens%20are%20heard.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Congress%20too%20welcomed%20the%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20decision%20to%20hold%20assembly%20elections%20by%20September%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20Congress%20has%20always%20demanded%20the%20restoration%20of%20full%20statehood%20for%20what%20has%20become%20the%20Union%20territory%20of%20Jammu%20%26amp%3B%20Kashmir.%20We%20welcome%20the%20SC%E2%80%99s%20verdict%20in%20this%20regard.%20Full%20statehood%20must%20be%20restored%20immediately.%20The%20aspirations%20of%20the%20people%20of%20Ladakh%20must%20also%20be%20fulfilled.%20We%20welcome%20the%20SC%E2%80%99s%20direction%20to%20hold%20the%20assembly%20elections.%20However%2C%20we%20believe%20the%20elections%20should%20be%20held%20immediately%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Chidambaram.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Aam%20Aadmi%20Party%20(AAP)%2C%20which%20had%20welcomed%20the%20Union%20government%E2%80%99s%20move%20on%20Article%20370%20in%202019%2C%20has%20not%20reacted%20to%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20judgement%20on%20the%20Union%20territories%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHigh%20drama%20in%20Rajya%20Sabha%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20there%20was%20high%20drama%20in%20the%20Rajya%20Sabha%20after%20DMK%20MP%20Mohamed%20Abdullah%20during%20the%20discussion%20on%20the%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20Reservation%20(Amendment)%20Bill%2C%202023%2C%20cited%20Article%203%20of%20the%20constitution%20and%20said%20that%20the%20abrogation%20of%20Article%20370%20%E2%80%9Cis%20an%20attack%20on%20federalism%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20cited%20the%202019%20Act%20that%20bifurcated%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20into%20two%20union%20territories%20as%20%E2%80%9Cunconstitutional%E2%80%9D%20citing%20Article%203.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETreasury%20benches%20then%20rose%20in%20protest%20and%20said%20that%20he%20is%20%E2%80%9Cnullifying%E2%80%9D%20the%20order%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERajya%20Sabha%20chair%20and%20vice%20president%20Jagdeep%20Dhankar%20rebuked%20Abdullah%20for%20%E2%80%9Cspeaking%20against%20the%20law%20of%20the%20land.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CHonourable%20member%20needs%20to%20be%20alive%20to%20the%20fact%20that%20in%20a%20historic%20judgement%20today%20the%20honourable%20Supreme%20Court%20has%20sustained%20what%20the%20Parliament%20has%20done%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Dhankar.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAnd%20therefore%20to%20speak%20against%20the%20judgement%2C%20which%20is%20the%20law%20of%20the%20land%2C%20is%20not%20appropriate.%20Your%20assertion%20was%20100%20per%20cent%20to%20the%20contrary.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAll%20of%20us%20must%20keep%20in%20mind%20that%20when%20the%20judiciary%20has%20taken%20a%20view%20on%20a%20particular%20issue%20comprehensively%2C%20decisively%2C%20we%20need%20to%20abide%20by%20it%2C%E2%80%9D%20Dhankhar%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAbdullah%20said%20that%20he%20had%20not%20gone%20into%20the%20judgement%20amid%20protests%20from%20the%20Treasury%20Benches.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECongress%20MP%20K.C.%20Venugopal%20supported%20Abdullah%E2%80%99s%20right%20to%20have%20a%20different%20point%20of%20view.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CHonourable%20court%20has%20given%20a%20judgement%20and%20we%20abide%20by%20it.%20We%20have%20a%20different%20point%20of%20view%20and%20he%20has%20a%20different%20point%20of%20view%2C%20but%20the%20member%20has%20the%20freedom%20to%20speak%20about%20it%20and%20criticise%20the%20judgement%20also.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDhankar%2C%20however%2C%20said%20that%20the%20MPs%E2%80%99%20%E2%80%9Cfreedom%20of%20speech%20in%20the%20house%20is%20not%20unqualified.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIt%20does%20not%20give%20you%20licence%20to%20say%20whatever%20you%20feel.%20You%20have%20to%20be%20accountable.%20How%20can%20anyone%20talk%20against%20a%20judgement%20given%20by%20the%20highest%20court%20of%20the%20land%3F%20We%20can%E2%80%99t%20ridicule%20a%20judgement%20like%20this.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EModi%20hails%20%E2%80%98historic%E2%80%99%20verdict%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20verdict%20has%20been%20hailed%20by%20the%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20(BJP)%2C%20including%20by%20Prime%20Minister%20Modi%20who%20called%20the%20decision%20%E2%80%9Chistoric%E2%80%9D%20and%20a%20%E2%80%9Cresounding%20declaration%20of%20hope%2C%20progress%20and%20unity%20for%20our%20sisters%20and%20brothe