ping%20for%20a%20fresh%20offensive%20in%20Gaza.%20This%20time%2C%20the%20south%20of%20the%20Gaza%20Strip%2C%20where%20civilians%20were%20advised%20to%20flee%20during%20the%20first%20six%20weeks%20of%20the%20military%20onslaught%2C%20was%20the%20main%20focus.%20Within%20four%20days%2C%20with%20tanks%20pushing%20into%20southern%20Gaza%2C%20the%20death%20toll%20was%20increasing%20by%20many%20hundreds%20every%20day%2C%20against%20an%20estimated%2015%2C000%20through%20the%20first%20six%20weeks.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20an%20article%20that%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjewishcurrents.org%2Fshabbat-reading-list%2Fdecember-1-2023-2-2%3Ftoken%3DXgyHlDG-Oqn5VMc8pPNte7NYDBt6h-9F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EJewish%20Currents%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cspan%3E%20described%20as%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20most%20important%20piece%20of%20journalism%E2%80%9D%20since%20the%20carnage%20began%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.972mag.com%2Fmass-assassination-factory-israel-calculated-bombing-gaza%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ea%20reporting%20coalition%20from%20two%20websites%2C%20%2B972%20and%20Local%20Call%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20tells%20of%20how%2C%20beginning%20October%208%2C%20the%20Israel%20Defence%20Force%20(IDF)%20shed%20all%20restraint%20and%20all%20pretence%20of%20abiding%20by%20the%20laws%20of%20war.%20There%20was%20an%20%E2%80%9Cexpanded%20authorisation%20for%20bombing%20non-military%20targets%2C%20the%20loosening%20of%20constraints%20regarding%20expected%20civilian%20casualties%2C%20and%20the%20use%20of%20an%20artificial%20intelligence%20system%20to%20generate%20more%20potential%20targets%20than%20ever%20before%E2%80%9D.%20All%20this%20contributed%20to%20destruction%20on%20an%20unimaginable%20scale.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ETargets%20were%20chosen%20with%20specific%20intent%20to%20diminish%20%E2%80%9CPalestinian%20civil%20society%E2%80%9D%2C%20or%20as%20a%20source%20tapped%20by%20the%20reporters%20put%20it%2C%20to%20%E2%80%9Ccreate%20a%20shock%E2%80%9D%20sufficient%20to%20%E2%80%9Clead%20civilians%20to%20put%20pressure%20on%20Hamas%E2%80%9D.%20Many%20of%20the%20sources%20who%20spoke%20on%20condition%20of%20anonymity%2C%20confirmed%20that%20Israel%20maintains%20files%20on%20every%20potential%20target%2C%20including%20homes.%20These%20%E2%80%9Cstipulate%20the%20number%20of%20civilians%20who%20are%20likely%20to%20be%20killed%20in%20an%20attack%20on%20a%20particular%20target%E2%80%9D%2C%20and%20every%20Israeli%20attack%20happens%20in%20full%20cognisance%20of%20the%20number%20of%20civilians%20%E2%80%9Ccertain%20to%20be%20killed%E2%80%9D.%20This%20number%20is%20%E2%80%9Ccalculated%20and%20known%20in%20advance%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20onslaught%20that%20resumed%20on%20December%201%20had%20the%20obvious%20object%20of%20making%20unfit%20for%20human%20life%20even%20the%20tiniest%20acreage%20that%20remained%20habitable.%20The%20infrastructure%20and%20amenities%20that%20made%20civic%20life%20possible%2C%20even%20in%20the%20most%20straitened%20circumstances%2C%20were%20to%20be%20systematically%20destroyed.%20And%20a%20consequence%20that%20is%20yet%20to%20be%20assessed%20is%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fsci-tech%2Fenergy-and-environment%2Fgaza-israel-invisible-environmental-war%2Farticle67576383.ece%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ethe%20environmental%20damage%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%3A%20the%20lasting%20toxicity%20that%20will%20be%20left%20in%20the%20soil%2C%20air%20and%20water%20of%20Gaza%20from%20this%20holocaust.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAway%20from%20the%20primary%20focus%2C%20Israel%20pushed%20ahead%20with%20plans%20in%20the%20West%20Bank%20to%20create%20a%20%E2%80%9Csecond%20Nakba%E2%80%9D%2C%20a%20mass%20expulsion%20of%20Palestinians.%20It%20involved%20longer-term%20planning%20than%20the%20military%20blitzkrieg%20underway%20in%20Gaza%2C%20and%20as%20the%20Israeli%20scholar%20of%20Tamil%20literature%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nybooks.com%2Farticles%2F2023%2F12%2F21%2Fa-bitter-season-in-the-west-bank-david-shulman%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EDavid%20Shulman%20put%20it%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20targeted%20the%20%E2%80%9Cdeliberate%20erosion%20of%20Palestinian%20civil%20society%20and%20institutions%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EGenocide%20is%20the%20clear%20object%2C%20and%20if%20intent%20is%20to%20be%20proven%2C%20Israelis%20starting%20with%20the%20top%20political%20leadership%2C%20have%20offered%20up%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FRezaNasri1%2Fstatus%2F1726650024698728573%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ea%20whole%20slew%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20of%20genocide%20adjacent%20statements%20since%20October%207.%20Gazans%20were%20children%20of%20darkness%2C%20while%20Israelis%20were%20children%20of%20light%2C%20said%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20Prime%20Minister%20Benjamin%20Netanyahu%2C%20who%20later%20invoked%20a%20Biblical%20story%20of%20treachery%20and%20retribution%20to%20warn%20Gaza%20of%20the%20scale%20of%20destruction%20beyond%20all%20humanly%20discernible%20dimensions.%20Defence%20minister%20Gallant%20spoke%20of%20a%20future%20for%20the%20Gaza%20Strip%20that%20would%20be%20unrecognisable%20since%20Israel%20intended%20to%20destroy%20everything%20in%20it.%20President%20Isaac%20Herzog%20dismissed%20any%20possibility%20of%20innocent%20civilian%20life%20in%20Gaza%20since%20everybody%20living%20there%20was%20ostensibly%20in%20moral%20solidarity%20with%20the%20militant%20resistance%20group%20Hamas.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EGideon%20Sa%E2%80%99ar%2C%20a%20former%20deputy%20prime%20minister%20now%20inducted%20into%20the%20wartime%20cabinet%2C%20spoke%20of%20Gaza%20ending%20up%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fforward.com%2Ffast-forward%2F564999%2Fisraeli-minister-gaza-must-be-smaller-saar%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eboth%20smaller%20and%20lesser%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20indicating%20that%20it%20would%20be%20abbreviated%20territorially%20and%20substantially%20depopulated.%20Danny%20Danon%2C%20a%20former%20ambassador%20to%20the%20UN%20who%20is%20now%20a%20member%20of%20the%20Israeli%20Knesset%2C%20spoke%20of%20the%20best%20humanitarian%20solution%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2FSaulStaniforth%2Fstatus%2F1726700704470012340%3Fs%3D20%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ebeing%20the%20dispersal%20of%20Gaza%E2%80%99s%20population%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20Countries%20that%20cared%20should%20step%20up%20to%20do%20their%20bit%20by%20taking%20in%20Palestinians%20from%20Gaza%20in%20their%20tens%20of%20thousands.%20With%20even%20greater%20crudity%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2Fmehdirhasan%2Fstatus%2F1727402884676071717%3Fs%3D20%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eformer%20Israeli%20cabinet%20minister%20Ayelet%20Shaked%20spoke%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20of%20converting%20the%20Khan%20Yunus%20refugee%20camp%20in%20Gaza%2C%20a%20teeming%20place%20of%20Palestinian%20settlement%20into%20a%20football%20field%2C%20and%20then%20%E2%80%9Ctaking%20advantage%20of%20the%20destruction%20that%20(Israel%20would)%20wreak%20upon%20them%20to%20tell%20the%20world%20that%20each%20country%20should%20take%20a%20defined%20quota%20%E2%80%A6%20We%20need%20two%20million%20to%20leave..%20Honestly%2C%20that%20is%20the%20solution%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F18123957%2FF8aEEn1WYAAtWt0.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F18123957%2FF8aEEn1WYAAtWt0.jpeg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F18123957%2FF8aEEn1WYAAtWt0-300x159.jpeg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F18123957%2FF8aEEn1WYAAtWt0-1024x544.jpeg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-680601%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22637%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EIsrael%20Prime%20Minister%20Benjamin%20Netanyahu.%20Photo%3A%20X%2F%40netanyahu%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIs%20this%20the%20brutal%20climax%20of%20the%20settler%20colonial%20project%20formally%20inaugurated%20in%20the%20Palestinian%20homeland%20in%201917%2C%20which%20gained%20a%20new%20impetus%20with%20the%20breakdown%20of%20the%20tenuous%20European%20order%20forged%20after%20World%20War%20I%3F%20From%20the%20declaration%20of%20the%20State%20of%20Israel%20in%201948%2C%20the%20brutal%20momentum%20of%20the%20settler%20project%20encountered%20headwinds%20from%20elsewhere%20in%20the%20world%2C%20where%20colonialism%20was%20being%20dismantled%20and%20new%20sovereign%20states%20coming%20into%20being.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIsrael%20came%20into%20existence%20on%20very%20different%20premises.%20And%20its%20origin%20story%20can%20be%20told%20on%20the%20smaller%20canvas%20of%20two%20towns%20in%20the%20south%20of%20Israel%2C%20Ashkelon%20and%20Sderot%2C%20that%20were%20among%20the%20worst%20affected%20when%20armed%20Hamas%20militants%20on%20October%207%2C%20surged%20across%20the%20heavy%20fortifications%20that%20fence%20Gaza%20in.%20As%20the%20attack%20was%20pushed%20back%20or%20defeated%2C%20the%20threat%20of%20rocket%20fire%20from%20Gaza%20persisted%2C%20leading%20to%20the%20quick%20evacuation%20of%20the%20more%20vulnerable%20residents%20in%20these%20towns.%20And%20then%20as%20the%20Israeli%20war%20machine%20prepared%20for%20retaliation%2C%20the%20citizens%20of%20the%20garrison%20state%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.jpost.com%2Fisrael-news%2Fdefense-news%2Farticle-767821%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ecelebrated%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20the%20exemplary%20display%20of%20solidarity%20in%20a%20time%20of%20adversity.%20In%20parts%20of%20the%20Arab%20world%2C%20the%20flight%20of%20Israeli%20nationals%20from%20the%20towns%20of%20Ashkelon%20and%20Sderot%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.saba.ye%2Fen%2Fnews3271914.htm%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ewas%20portrayed%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20as%20the%20retreat%20of%20usurpers.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20proclamation%20of%20the%20State%20of%20Israel%20involved%20the%20forced%20transfer%20of%20an%20estimated%20750%2C000%20Palestinians%2C%20who%20either%20crossed%20the%20borders%20into%20neighbouring%20countries%2C%20or%20crowded%20into%20the%20West%20Bank%20and%20Gaza.%20Israel%20disclaims%20all%20blame%2C%20entirely%20faulting%20the%20Arab%20leadership%20in%20Palestine%20and%20elsewhere%20for%20the%20humanitarian%20catastrophe.%20Convinced%20that%20the%20small%20Zionist%20force%20assembled%20in%20Palestine%20would%20be%20no%20match%20for%20their%20armies%2C%20the%20Arab%20states%20allegedly%20encouraged%20the%20mass%20displacement%2C%20on%20the%20assurance%20that%20military%20victory%20was%20certain%20and%20resettlement%20would%20quickly%20follow.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20Read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhistory%2Fresisting-the-zionist-revisionism-of-gandhi%5C%22%3EResisting%20the%20Zionist%20Revisionism%20of%20Gandhi%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20reality%20as%20Israeli%20historians%20Benny%20Morris%20and%20Ilan%20Pappe%20have%20established%2C%20from%20radically%20opposing%20perspectives%2C%20is%20that%20the%20Jewish%20National%20Agency%2C%20which%20in%20subsequent%20years%20became%20the%20Government%20of%20Israel%2C%20had%20a%20blueprint%20to%20effect%20the%20near%20complete%20conquest%20of%20territory%20seen%20as%20essential%20to%20the%20strategic%20defence%20of%20Israel%20as%20a%20Jewish%20state.%20This%20required%20the%20near-complete%20expulsion%20of%20Arabs.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBenny%20Morris%20writes%20as%20an%20unreconstructed%20Zionist%2C%20picks%20and%20chooses%20his%20sources%20from%20the%20IDF%20archives%20and%20concludes%2C%20regretfully%2C%20that%20the%20job%20was%20only%20half-done%2C%20leaving%20Israel%20with%20an%20insoluble%20demographic%20conundrum.%20Ilan%20Pappe%20sees%20the%20ethnic%20cleansing%2C%20approved%20at%20the%20highest%20level%20of%20the%20Zionist%20leadership%2C%20as%20an%20injustice%20that%20calls%20for%20restitution.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20first%20phase%20of%20the%20aggression%20involved%20the%20areas%20designated%20as%20Jewish%20under%20the%20UN%20Partition%20Plan%20of%20November%201947.%20The%20UN%20General%20Assembly%20had%20been%20more%20than%20generous.%20The%20Jewish%20people%2C%20though%20less%20than%2030%25%20of%20the%20population%20of%20Palestine%20%E2%80%93%20despite%20the%20surge%20in%20numbers%20after%20World%20War%20II%20%E2%80%93%20were%20given%2055%25%20of%20the%20land%20area.%20The%20designated%20Jewish%20area%20still%20had%20a%20majority%20of%20Arabs%2C%20while%20the%20designated%20Arab%20area%20had%20a%20Jewish%20population%20of%20less%20than%2010%25.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Zionist%20plan%20was%20personally%20approved%20by%20the%20first%20prime%20minister%20of%20Israel%2C%20David%20Ben-Gurion%2C%20and%20carried%20out%20by%20the%20Haganah%2C%20a%20clandestine%20militia%20that%20had%20achieved%20some%20form%20of%20recognition%20by%20the%20British%20authorities%20during%20the%20Palestinian%20intifada%20of%20the%201930s%2C%20and%20later%20became%20the%20nucleus%20of%20the%20IDF.%20Ben-Gurion%E2%80%99s%20intent%20was%20very%20clear%20soon%20after%20the%20Royal%20Commission%20appointed%20by%20the%20British%20to%20deal%20with%20an%20intractable%20conflict%20of%20their%20own%20creation%2C%20proposed%20the%20partition%20of%20Palestine%20in%201937.%20Though%20the%20plan%20fell%20well%20short%20of%20Ben-Gurion%E2%80%99s%20ambitions%2C%20he%20was%20prepared%20to%20bide%20his%20time.%20In%20October%201937%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.foreignpolicyjournal.com%2F2016%2F11%2F14%2Fbenny-morriss-untenable-denial-of-the-ethnic-cleansing-of-palestine%2F%23_ednref17%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ehe%20wrote%20to%20his%20son%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20conceding%20that%20the%20partition%20gave%20him%20%E2%80%9Cno%20pleasure%E2%80%9D.%20Yet%20the%20land%20was%20%E2%80%9Cnot%20in%20our%20actual%20possession%E2%80%9D%2C%20and%20what%20was%20%E2%80%9Cin%20actual%20possession%E2%80%9D%20was%20%E2%80%9Cless%20than%20what%20they%20(were)%20proposing%20for%20a%20Jewish%20state%E2%80%9D.%20If%20he%20were%20an%20Arab%2C%20he%20%E2%80%9Cwould%20have%20been%20very%20indignant%E2%80%9D%2C%20but%20being%20in%20the%20position%20he%20was%2C%20he%20would%20be%20satisfied%20with%20getting%20%E2%80%9Cmore%20than%20what%20we%20already%20have%E2%80%9D%2C%20though%20%E2%80%9Cmuch%20less%20than%20we%20merit%20and%20desire%E2%80%9D.%20The%20Zionist%20plan%20was%20%E2%80%9Cnot%20that%20the%20land%20remain%20whole%20and%20unified%E2%80%9D%2C%20but%20that%20the%20%E2%80%9Cwhole%20and%20unified%20land%20be%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EJewish%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9D%20(emphases%20in%20original).%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhile%20waiting%20for%20that%20time%20when%20the%20whole%20of%20the%20land%20would%20be%20Jewish%2C%20Ben-Gurion%20was%20clear%20about%20what%20the%20%E2%80%9Csolution%20of%20the%20question%20of%20the%20Arabs%E2%80%9D%20would%20be%3A%20%E2%80%9CI%20am%20for%20their%20compulsory%20transfer%E2%80%9D%2C%20he%20said%20at%20a%20meeting%20of%20the%20Jewish%20Agency%3A%20%E2%80%9CI%20do%20not%20see%20anything%20immoral%20in%20it%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOnce%20the%20UN%20partition%20plan%20was%20announced%2C%20the%20Jewish%20Agency%20hurried%20into%20action.%20Numerous%20villages%20within%20the%20designated%20Jewish%20area%20were%20identified%20and%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.in%2FEthnic-Cleansing-Palestine-Ilan-Pappe-ebook%2Fdp%2FB00KT5W342%2Fref%3Dsr_1_2%3Fcrid%3D24O5D2F1JNK4T%26keywords%3Dilan%2Bpappe%2Bthe%2Bethnic%2Bcleansing%2Bof%2Bilan%2Bpappe%2Bthe%2Bethnic%2Bcleansing%2Bof%2Bpalestinepalestine%26nsdOptOutParam%3Dtrue%26qid%3D1701937601%26sprefix%3Dilan%2Bpappe%2Bthe%2Bethnic%2Bcleansing%2Bof%2Bilan%2Bpappe%2Bthe%2Bethnic%2Bcleansing%2Bof%2Bpalestinepalestine%252Caps%252C196%26sr%3D8-2%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EIlan%20Pappe%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20(2007%3A%20104-5)%20provides%20the%20details%20of%20the%20Haganah%20strategy.%20Picked%20for%20early%20attention%20was%20Khisas%2C%20a%20%E2%80%9Csmall%20village%20with%20a%20few%20hundred%20Muslims%20and%20one%20hundred%20Christians%E2%80%9D%2C%20known%20for%20the%20%E2%80%9Cnatural%20beauty%20of%20its%20location%E2%80%9D.%20Late%20on%20December%2018%2C%201947%2C%20Haganah%20troops%20attacked%2C%20randomly%20%E2%80%9Cblowing%20up%20houses%E2%80%9D%20as%20the%20village%20slept.%20A%20reporter%20of%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ENew%20York%20Times%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3Ewho%20witnessed%20the%20aftermath%20and%20closely%20followed%20subsequent%20events%2C%20queried%20the%20Haganah%2C%20but%20was%20met%20with%20stout%20denial.%20In%20the%20face%20of%20his%20persistence%2C%20Ben-Gurion%20%E2%80%9Cissued%20a%20dramatic%20public%20apology%2C%20claiming%20the%20action%20had%20been%20unauthorised%E2%80%9D.%20Just%20a%20few%20months%20later%20in%20a%20public%20speech%2C%20he%20listed%20it%20among%20the%20successful%20operations%20carried%20out%20by%20his%20military%20wing.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20Khisas%20operation%20followed%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.jstor.org%2Fstable%2F2537591%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ethe%20blueprint%20of%20Plan%20C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20adopted%20by%20the%20Zionist%20leadership%20in%20May%201946%20and%20executed%20by%20the%20Haganah%20from%20about%20the%20middle%20of%201947.%20The%20typical%20mode%20for%20carrying%20out%20military%20operations%20was%20laid%20out%20in%20clear%20detail%3A%20%E2%80%9C..%20the%20village%20will%20be%20surrounded%20by%20a%20force%20whose%20size%20will%20vary%20with%20the%20circumference%20of%20the%20village%20and%20the%20resistance%20expected%20%E2%80%A6.%20A%20part%20of%20this%20force%20%E2%80%93%20at%20least%20half%20%E2%80%93%20will%20enter%20the%20village%20and%20carry%20out%20acts%20of%20sabotage%20by%20setting%20fire%20to%20and%20blowing%20up%20targets.%20If%20the%20objective%20is%20general%20punitive%20action%2C%20everything%20possible%20should%20be%20set%20on%20fire%20and%20the%20houses%20of%20the%20instigators%20and%20participants%20in%20operations%20must%20be%20demolished%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F11155943%2F1148px-Labor_Party_Convention_in_preparation_for_the_forthcoming_general_elections_FL45758585.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221148%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F11155943%2F1148px-Labor_Party_Convention_in_preparation_for_the_forthcoming_general_elections_FL45758585.jpg%201148w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F11155943%2F1148px-Labor_Party_Convention_in_preparation_for_the_forthcoming_general_elections_FL45758585-300x188.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F11155943%2F1148px-Labor_Party_Convention_in_preparation_for_the_forthcoming_general_elections_FL45758585-1024x642.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-688652%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22720%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EDavid%20Ben-Gurion.%20Photo%3A%20Dan%20Hadani%20collection%2C%20National%20Library%20of%20Israel%2FWikimedia%20Commons%2C%20CC%20BY%204.0%2C%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20ethnic%20cleansing%20model%20adopted%20in%20urban%20areas%20is%20described%20in%20the%20context%20of%20Haifa%2C%20then%20Palestine%E2%80%99s%20third%20largest%20city%2C%20by%20Ilan%20Pappe%20(2007%3A%20105).%20%E2%80%9CFrom%20the%20morning%20after%20the%20UN%20Partition%20Resolution%20was%20adopted%E2%80%9D%2C%20he%20writes%2C%20%E2%80%9Cthe%2075%2C000%20Palestinians%20in%20the%20city%20were%20subjected%20to%20a%20campaign%20of%20terror%E2%80%9D.%20The%20Haganah%20was%20joined%20in%20this%20enterprise%20by%20the%20terror%20group%20Irgun%2C%20led%20by%20the%20future%20Prime%20Minister%2C%20Menachem%20Begin%20and%20drawing%20inspiration%20from%20Vladimir%20Jabotinsky%E2%80%99s%20rival%20Zionist%20stream.%20Since%20the%20Jewish%20residents%20were%20relatively%20new%20to%20the%20town%2C%20they%20had%20occupied%20higher%20reaches%20along%20the%20hill%20slopes.%20A%20typical%20tactic%20was%20to%20pour%20oil%20and%20fuel%20down%20the%20roads%2C%20which%20would%20be%20ignited%2C%20and%20%E2%80%9Cwhen%20panic-stricken%20Palestinians%20came%20running%20out%20of%20their%20homes%20to%20try%20to%20extinguish%20these%20rivers%20of%20fire%2C%20they%20were%20sprayed%20by%20machine-gun%20fire%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.jstor.org%2Fstable%2F4327736%23%3A~%3Atext%3DD%2520URING%2520the%2520early%2520months%2C70%252C000%2520remained%2520in%2520the%2520city.%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EBenny%20Morris%20records%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20that%20by%20July%2C%20two%20months%20after%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20declaration%20of%20independence%2C%20%E2%80%9Conly%20some%203%2C500%20of%20Haifa%E2%80%99s%20prewar%20Arab%20population%20of%2070%2C000%20remained%20in%20the%20city%E2%80%9D.%20The%20flight%20began%20in%20December%201947%2C%20but%20the%20April%20that%20followed%20was%20especially%20catastrophic%2C%20when%20the%20Haganah%20laid%20siege%20to%20the%20city%20and%20finally%20conquered%20it.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBen-Gurion%20had%20clearly%20spelt%20out%20how%20he%20saw%20the%20future%20of%20the%20city%20when%20he%20visited%20early%20in%20May.%20The%20number%20of%20Palestinians%20was%20not%20to%20exceed%2015%2C000%2C%20of%20which%20%E2%80%9Ctwo-thirds%20would%20be%20Christians%2C%20one-third%20Moslems%E2%80%9D.%20These%20communities%20were%20to%20be%20concentrated%20in%20two%20distinct%20parts%20of%20the%20city.%20In%20the%20months%20that%20followed%2C%20these%20plans%20of%20%E2%80%9Cdisplacement%20and%20concentration%E2%80%9D%20were%20carried%20out%20by%20newly%20empowered%20Jewish%20military%20administrators.%20The%20depopulation%20project%20moreover%2C%20was%20even%20more%20successful%20than%20envisaged.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Palestinian%20historian%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-jstor-org.opj.remotlog.com%2Fstable%2F2537591%3FsearchText%3DWalid%2BKhalidi%252C%2BPlan%2BDalet%252C%2BMaster-Plan%2Bfor%2Bthe%2BConquest%2Bof%2BPalestine%26searchUri%3D%252Faction%252FdoBasicSearch%253FQuery%253DWalid%252BKhalidi%25252C%252BPlan%252BDalet%25252C%252BMaster-Plan%252Bfor%252Bthe%252BConquest%252Bof%252BPalestine%26ab_segments%3D0%252Fbasic_search_gsv2%252Fcontrol%26refreqid%3Dfastly-default%253Ac1d3fe6f35d6d3a702af5a647596c1d7%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EWalid%20Khalidi%20documents%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20how%20the%20Zionist%20aggression%20under%20the%20guidance%20of%20Plan%20D%20scaled%20new%20heights%20as%20the%20British%20departure%20neared.%20For%20all%20the%20military%20operations%20that%20had%20been%20carried%20out%20till%20then%2C%20results%20were%20modest%20in%20terms%20of%20the%20vacant%20spaces%20created%20for%20Jewish%20occupation.%20Plan%20D%20involved%20actions%20outside%20the%20area%20designated%20as%20Jewish%20under%20the%20UN%20Partition%20Plan.%20Brigade%20commanders%20of%20the%20Haganah%2C%20working%20in%20collaboration%20with%20the%20Irgun%20and%20other%20armed%20terrorist%20groups%2C%20were%20granted%20the%20authority%20to%20mount%20%E2%80%9Coperations%20against%20enemy%20population%20centers%20inside%20or%20near%20(the%20Zionist)%20defensive%20system%20in%20order%20to%20prevent%20them%20from%20being%20used%20as%20bases%20by%20an%20active%20armed%20force%E2%80%9D.%20The%20options%20included%20the%20%E2%80%9Cdestruction%20of%20villages%E2%80%A6%20setting%20fire%20to%2C%20blowing%20up%2C%20and%20planting%20mines%20in%20the%20debris%E2%80%9D.%20Brigade%20commanders%20were%20also%20authorised%20to%20mount%20%E2%80%9Ccombing%20and%20control%20operations%E2%80%9D%20which%20could%20proceed%20by%20the%20%E2%80%9Cencirclement%20of%20the%20village%E2%80%9D.%20In%20the%20event%20that%20resistance%20was%20encountered%20while%20%E2%80%9Cconducting%20a%20search%E2%80%9D%2C%20the%20military%20units%20were%20empowered%20to%20%E2%80%9Cwipe%20out%E2%80%9D%20the%20opposing%20force%2C%20and%20%E2%80%9Cexpel%E2%80%9D%20the%20population%20%E2%80%9Coutside%20the%20borders%20of%20the%20state%E2%80%9D.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESderot%20stands%20where%20the%20two%20Palestinian%20villages%20of%20Huj%20and%20Najd%20once%20stood.%20Soon%20after%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20declaration%20of%20independence%2C%20Hagana%20forces%20cleared%20out%20the%20village%20of%20Najd.%20With%20the%20expected%20advance%20of%20Egyptian%20forces%20%E2%80%9Cjust%20hours%20away%E2%80%9D%2C%20records%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.in%2F1948-History-First-Arab-Israeli-War%2Fdp%2F0300151128%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EBenny%20Morris%20(2008%3A%20161)%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20the%20IDF%E2%80%99s%20Negev%20Brigade%20%E2%80%9Cconquered%20the%20village%20of%20Burayr%2C%20apparently%20(sic)%20committing%20atrocities%20and%20killing%20several%20dozen%20villagers%2C%20and%20drove%20out%20the%20inhabitants%20of%20the%20nearby%20villages%20of%20Sumsum%20and%20Najd%E2%80%9D.%20A%20fortnight%20later%2C%20the%20same%20IDF%20unit%20%E2%80%9Craided%20the%20neighbouring%20villages%20of%20Muharraqa%20and%20Kaufakha%2C%20driving%20out%20the%20inhabitants%2C%20and%20conquered%20Beit%20Tima%20and%20Huj%2C%20a%20%E2%80%98friendly%E2%80%99%20village%20that%20%E2%80%A6%20commanders%20nonetheless%20believed%20posed%20a%20danger%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EEthnic%20cleansing%20was%20consistent%20with%20the%20mandate%20handed%20down%20from%20the%20top%20level%20of%20the%20Zionist%20leadership%2C%20to%20create%20the%20widest%20possible%20territorial%20expanse%20with%20minimal%20encumbrance%20of%20Palestinian%20people.%20Plan%20D%20was%20quite%20clearly%2C%20an%20effort%20through%20active%20military%20operations%20to%20fulfil%20the%20Zionist%20fever%20dream%20that%20Palestine%20was%20a%20%E2%80%9Cland%20without%20a%20people%E2%80%9D%2C%20that%20the%20Jews%20as%20a%20%E2%80%9Cpeople%20without%20a%20land%E2%80%9D%2C%20had%20divine%20mandate%20over.%20The%20ethnic%20cleansing%20of%20Huj%20and%20Najd%20and%20other%20proximate%20villages%20never%20regarded%20as%20a%20military%20threat%2C%20had%20a%20strategic%20purpose.%20Benny%20Morris%20quotes%20the%20secretary-general%20of%20the%20Arab%20League%20at%20the%20time%20complaining%20that%20the%20purpose%20of%20the%20ethnic%20cleansing%20was%20to%20create%20human%20shields%20against%20the%20expected%20entry%20of%20Egyptian%20armed%20forces.%20That%20was%20indeed%2C%20the%20%E2%80%9Cgrim%20logic%E2%80%9D%2C%20writes%20Morris%2C%20to%20drive%20out%20%E2%80%9Cinhabitants%20from%20areas%20on%20or%20near%20roads%20by%20which%20Arab%20regular%20forces%20could%20enter%20the%20country%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20town%20currently%20known%20as%20Ashkelon%20had%20its%20day%20of%20reckoning%20with%20Plan%20D%20a%20little%20later.%20It%20fell%20to%20Egyptian%20control%20soon%20after%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20declaration%20of%20independence%20and%20was%20attacked%20by%20artillery%20and%20air%20till%20November%201948%2C%20when%20the%20IDF%20finally%20completed%20its%20conquest.%20Palestinian%20scholar%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FLand-Without-People-Palestinians-1949-1996%2Fdp%2F0571191002%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3ENur%20Masalha%20(1997%3A%209)%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20provides%20the%20essential%20details.%20Known%20till%201950%20as%20Al-Majdal%2C%20Ashkelon%20had%20till%20the%20eve%20of%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20declaration%20of%20independence%2C%20a%20population%20of%2010%2C000.%20It%20was%20emptied%20out%20to%20some%20degree%20during%20the%20IDF%20bombardment%20though%20after%20the%20armistice%20of%201949%2C%20still%20had%20a%20population%20of%202%2C700.%20It%20was%20then%20designated%20as%20a%20town%20for%20the%20resettlement%20of%20immigrant%20Jews%20from%20other%20parts%20of%20West%20Asia%20and%20North%20Africa.%20In%20February%201949%2C%20an%20officially%20constituted%20committee%20decided%20to%20empty%20the%20town%20of%20all%20Arabs.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EA%20Jew%20from%20Iraq%2C%20promised%20resettlement%20in%20the%20area%2C%20recalled%20being%20continually%20reassured%20by%20the%20Zionist%20administration%20that%20al-Majdal%20would%20be%20vacated%20of%20all%20Arabs%2C%20clearing%20space%20for%20him%20to%20occupy.%20Masalha%20(1997%3A%2010)%20records%20how%20this%20newly%20arrived%20Iraqi%20Jew%20was%20uneasy%20at%20the%20thought%20and%20found%20an%20equal%20sense%20of%20mystification%20in%20the%20course%20of%20a%20conversation%20with%20an%20Al-Majdal%20resident.%20There%20seemed%20no%20reason%2C%20he%20thought%2C%20for%20expelling%20a%20family%20that%20had%20been%20resident%20in%20the%20town%20for%20generations%2C%20perfectly%20willing%20to%20assume%20citizenship%20of%20the%20new%20sovereign.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EDescendants%20of%20Al-Majdal%2C%20Huj%20and%20Najd%20are%20today%20crowded%20into%20Gaza%2C%20a%20narrow%20strip%20of%20territory%20that%20the%20Egyptian%20army%20managed%20to%20hold%20when%20an%20armistice%20in%20February%201949%20ended%20the%20war%20on%20that%20front.%20The%20larger%20part%20of%20the%20Gaza%20district%2C%20which%20was%20awarded%20to%20the%20Palestinians%20in%20its%20entirety%20under%20the%20UN%20Partition%20Plan%2C%20fell%20to%20Israel.%20A%20truce%20with%20other%20Arab%20states%20followed%2C%20though%20expulsion%20continued%20to%20be%20on%20the%20active%20agenda%20of%20the%20Israeli%20state.%20The%20refugees%E2%80%99%20right%20of%20return%20was%20enshrined%20in%20UN%20Security%20Council%20Resolution%20194%2C%20adopted%20unanimously%20in%201949%20and%20reiterated%20every%20year%20till%201967%2C%20though%20Israel%20has%20faced%20little%20consequence%20for%20ignoring%20it%20in%20its%20obsession%20with%20ethnic%20purity.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F26153147%2F1200px-Flickr_-_Government_Press_Office_GPO_-_Arab_People_fleeing.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F26153147%2F1200px-Flickr_-_Government_Press_Office_GPO_-_Arab_People_fleeing.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F26153147%2F1200px-Flickr_-_Government_Press_Office_GPO_-_Arab_People_fleeing-300x202.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F26153147%2F1200px-Flickr_-_Government_Press_Office_GPO_-_Arab_People_fleeing-1024x689.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-681847%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22807%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EPalestinians%20fleeing%20their%20homes%20after%20the%20establishment%20of%20Israel%20in%201948.%20Photo%3A%20Wikimedia%20Commons%2FDavid%20Eldan%2FCC%20BY-SA%203.0%20DEED%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHome%20to%20about%2070%2C000%20before%20the%20creation%20of%20Israel%2C%20Gaza%20found%20itself%20dealing%20with%20an%20influx%20of%20over%20200%2C000.%20Palestinian%20villages%20in%20the%20south%20of%20Israel%20continued%20being%20emptied%20out%20in%20the%20years%20after%2C%20with%20most%20residents%20being%20transferred%20to%20Gaza.%20In%201956%2C%20Britain%20and%20France%20joined%20forces%20in%20an%20effort%20at%20forcing%20the%20newly%20installed%20Egyptian%20leader%2C%20Gamal%20Abdel%20Nasser%2C%20to%20back%20away%20from%20his%20nationalisation%20of%20the%20Suez%20Canal.%20Israel%20joined%20the%20military%20misadventure%20with%20its%20own%20agenda%20of%20territorial%20aggrandisement.%20Gaza%20and%20the%20Sinai%20were%20occupied%20in%20no%20time%20and%20at%20little%20cost%2C%20but%20as%20Masalha%20(1997%3A%2038-41)%20records%2C%20Ben-Gurion%20could%20hardly%20conceal%20his%20disappointment%20with%20the%20%E2%80%9Cdemographic%20outcome%E2%80%9D.%20On%20his%20first%20visit%20to%20the%20newly%20conquered%20territory%2C%20%E2%80%9Ca%20new%20reality%20was%20revealed%20before%20his%20eyes%2C%20which%20shocked%20him%20deeply%3A%20the%20Palestinians%20did%20not%20flee%20from%20the%20IDF%20as%20they%20had%20in%201948%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBetween%20then%20and%201957%2C%20when%20it%20was%20forced%20to%20withdraw%20by%20the%20US%2C%20yet%20to%20sign%20up%20as%20an%20unconditional%20source%20of%20sustenance%20and%20support%2C%20Israel%20did%20its%20best%20to%20%E2%80%9Cterrorise%20the%20Palestinians%20into%20fleeing%20from%20the%20teeming%20refugee%20camps%E2%80%9D.%20Two%20incidents%20in%20particular%2C%20at%20Khan%20Yunis%20and%20Rafah%2C%20involved%20the%20killing%20of%20hundreds%20of%20Palestinian%20civilians.%20After%20the%20Israeli%20withdrawal%2C%20a%20mass%20grave%20was%20unearthed%20at%20Khan%20Yunis%2C%20with%20the%20%E2%80%9Cbodies%20of%20forty%20Arabs%20who%20had%20been%20shot%20in%20the%20back%20of%20their%20head%20after%20their%20hands%20had%20been%20tied%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EDemography%20has%20been%20a%20constant%20obsession%20with%20Israel%20since%20its%20creation.%20Ben-Gurion%20and%20his%20successors%2C%20always%20intent%20on%20all%20of%20the%20land%2C%20faced%20an%20intractable%20problem%20of%20numbers%20when%20that%20territorial%20dream%20was%20fulfilled.%20For%20roughly%20two%20decades%20after%20it%20provoked%20and%20decisively%20won%20the%20Six-Day%20War%20against%20neighbouring%20Arab%20states%2C%20Zionism%20seemed%20to%20settle%20into%20another%20kind%20of%20compact%20with%20the%20Palestinians%2C%20treating%20the%20occupied%20people%20as%20a%20reservoir%20of%20low-wage%20labour%20to%20fuel%20the%20Israeli%20economy.%20But%20that%20was%20an%20unstable%20arrangement%2C%20always%20likely%20to%20fray%20in%20a%20situation%20of%20the%20constant%20denial%20of%20basic%20rights.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.jstor.org%2Fstable%2F2537340%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20a%20research%20article%20published%20in%201989%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20a%20civil%20rights%20campaigner%20observed%20that%20a%20movement%20had%20begun%20emerging%20afresh%20in%20Jewish%20society%2C%20which%20supported%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20idea%20of%20expelling%20all%20Palestinians%20from%20the%20West%20Bank%20and%20Gaza%20Strip%20to%20neighbouring%20Arab%20countries%20or%2C%20preferably%2C%20beyond%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EToday%2C%20with%20the%20non-Jewish%20population%20in%20Palestine%20probably%20in%20a%20majority%2C%20the%20State%20of%20Israel%20is%20called%20upon%20to%20shed%20its%20pretence%20of%20being%20a%20democracy%2C%20always%20a%20shallow%20one.%20Hiving%20off%20the%20West%20Bank%20and%20Gaza%20as%20an%20autonomous%20and%20demilitarised%20Palestinian%20state%2C%20was%20a%20brief%20promise%2C%20insincere%20and%20fraudulent%20at%20the%20best%20of%20times.%20Israel%20is%20aware%20that%20the%20wounds%20it%20has%20inflicted%20are%20too%20raw%2C%20to%20ever%20feel%20secure%20within%20the%20boundaries%20established%20in%201948.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Palestine%20Liberation%20Organisation%2C%20helmed%20by%20the%20largest%20resistance%20group%20Fatah%2C%20was%20given%20the%20option%20of%20being%20a%20caretaker%20of%20the%20Israeli%20occupation%2C%20a%20lesser%20body%20attending%20to%20municipal%20chores%2C%20but%20primarily%20ensuring%20the%20security%20of%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20territory%20and%20its%20settlements.%20Fatah%20played%20along%20but%20at%20some%20point%20called%20off%20the%20farce.%20Israel%20has%20ever%20since%20been%20pushing%20for%20the%20settlement%20it%20always%20had%20in%20mind%3A%20unilateral%20separation%2C%20under%20which%20Gaza%20would%20remain%20in%20a%20permanent%20state%20of%20siege%2C%20and%20the%20West%20Bank%20would%20be%20a%20thick%20patchwork%20of%20Jewish%20settlements%20with%20segregated%20routes%20of%20access%20only%20for%20Jews.%20October%207%20was%20a%20unilateral%20abridgement%20of%20the%20script%20from%20the%20Palestinian%20side.%20It%20has%20accelerated%20the%20quest%20for%20a%20%E2%80%9Cfinal%20solution%E2%80%9D%20that%20brings%20all%20the%20genocidal%20nightmares%20of%20the%20past%20back%20in%20vivid%20horror.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fauthor%2Fsukumar-muralidharan%5C%22%3ESukumar%20Muralidharan%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20an%20independent%20writer%20and%20researcher%20based%20in%20the%20Delhi%20region.%20He%20has%20worked%20in%20print%20media%2C%20as%20a%20journalism%20instructor%20and%20trainer%2C%20and%20press%20freedom%20campaigner.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702299604000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F11160252%2FGA6xi9-WoAEKSsS.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fgaza-brutal-climax-zionist-settler-colonial-project-israel%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20complete%20expulsion%20of%20Palestinians%20has%20long%20been%20a%20goal%20of%20Israel's%20political%20leaders.%C2%A0%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A27%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fgaza-brutal-climax-zionist-settler-colonial-project-israel%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22US%20anti-missile%20base%20in%20Poland%20to%20start%20operations%20-%20Polish%20PM%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702299133000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fichef.bbci.co.uk%2Fnews%2F1024%2Fbranded_news%2F12617%2Fproduction%2F_131978257_gettyimages-531224480.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-europe-67681947%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Redzikowo%20Air%20Base%20will%20become%20the%20US's%20second%20anti-missile%20base%20in%20Europe%2C%20after%20another%20in%20southern%20Romania.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A68%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-europe-67681947%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-bbc-co-uk.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-europe-67681947.amp%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-europe-67681947.amp%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Did%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20Follow%20Due%20Process%20While%20Expelling%20Mahua%20Moitra%20From%20the%20House%3F%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F11163835%2FScreenshot-2023-12-11-at-4.37.14-PM.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3ELok%20Sabha%20MP%20Mahua%20Moitra%20lost%20membership%20of%20the%20House%20on%20December%208%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20a%20report%20from%20the%20parliamentary%20ethics%20committee%2C%20which%20held%20her%20conduct%20to%20%E2%80%98unethical%E2%80%99%20and%20in%20%E2%80%98contempt%20of%20the%20House%E2%80%99.%20The%20panel%20had%20recommended%20her%20expulsion.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDid%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20%E2%80%93%20a%20law-making%20body%20%E2%80%93%20follow%20the%20due%20process%20of%20law%20in%20expelling%20her%3F%20She%20allegedly%20asked%20certain%20questions%20in%20parliament%20because%20she%20was%20taking%20cash%20and%20gifts%20from%20Darshan%20Hiranandani%2C%20an%20Indian%20industrialist%20operating%20from%20Dubai.%20She%20faced%20accusations%20of%20sharing%20with%20him%20her%20login%20and%20password%2C%20meant%20for%20MPs%20to%20access%20the%20web%20portal%20used%20by%20parliamentarians.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECash%20trail%20issue%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20ethics%20committee%20had%20no%20conclusive%20evidence%20of%20a%20cash%20trail%20leading%20to%20Mitra%2C%20and%20asked%20the%20investigating%20agencies%20such%20as%20the%20Central%20Bureau%20of%20Investigation%20and%20Enforcement%20Directorate%20to%20unearth%20this%20trail.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202005%20cash%20for%20query%20scam%2C%2011%20MPs%20%E2%80%93%20six%20from%20the%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%2C%20three%20from%20the%20Bahujan%20Samaj%20Party%20and%20one%20each%20from%20the%20Rashtriya%20Janata%20Dal%20and%20Congress%20%E2%80%93%20were%20involved.%20One%20belonged%20to%20the%20Rajya%20Sabha.%20All%20of%20them%20were%20expelled%20from%20the%20House%20based%20on%20conclusive%20evidence%20captured%20in%20%3Cem%3ECobra%20Post%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%99s%20sting%20operation%2C%20which%20showed%20them%20receiving%20money%20for%20asking%20questions.%20The%20BJP%20described%20it%20as%20a%20kangaroo%20court%20verdict%20and%20L.K.%20Advani%2C%20while%20admitting%20the%20corruption%20aspects%20of%20the%20case%2C%20dubbed%20the%20expulsion%20the%20%E2%80%9Cparliamentary%20equivalent%20of%20capital%20punishment%E2%80%9D.%20In%202005%2C%20the%20sole%20determining%20factor%20for%20expelling%20those%20MPs%20was%20cash%20they%20received%20for%20asking%20questions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20allegation%20that%20Mitra%20received%20money%20is%20unproven%2C%20and%20so%20the%20decision%20to%20expel%20her%20raises%20questions%20about%20the%20fairness%20of%20the%20process%20and%20procedure%20followed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENo%20cross%20examination%20of%20Hiranandani%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHiranandani%E2%80%99s%20charge%20in%20his%20affidavit%20submitted%20before%20the%20ethics%20committee%20that%20he%20gave%20extensive%20gifts%20to%20Mitra%20make%20him%20as%20much%20culpable%20as%20a%20bribe-giver%20as%20Mitra%20as%20a%20recipient%20of%20those%20gifts.%20Her%20request%20to%20the%20committee%20to%20cross-examine%20him%20on%20the%20charges%20he%20hurled%20at%20her%20was%20not%20granted.%20The%20due%20process%20of%20dispensing%20justice%20mandating%20that%20the%20accused%20has%20a%20right%20to%20cross%20examine%20the%20person%20making%20allegations%20should%20have%20been%20followed.%20Did%20the%20ethics%20committee%2C%20as%20a%20mini%20parliament%20forming%20part%20of%20the%20apex%20legislature%20making%20law%20for%20the%20nation%2C%20adhere%20to%20the%20basic%20legal%20process%20while%20dealing%20with%20the%20Moitra%E2%80%99s%20case%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22(At%20Least)%20Three%20Critical%20Flaws%20in%20the%20Ethics%20Committee%20Report%20on%20Mahua%20Moitra%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fat-least-three-critical-flaws-in-the-ethics-committee-report-on-mahua-moitra%5C%22%3E(At%20Least)%20Three%20Critical%20Flaws%20in%20the%20Ethics%20Committee%20Report%20on%20Mahua%20Moitra%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIssue%20of%20sharing%20login%20and%20password%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDid%20Moitra%2C%20by%20sharing%20her%20login%20and%20password%20to%20the%20MP%20portal%2C%20breach%20any%20rules%20or%20procedures%20of%20parliament%3F%20Neither%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20nor%20Rajya%20Sabha%20has%20any%20rule%20or%20procedure%20governing%20this%20aspect.%20In%20the%20absence%20of%20any%20such%20rule%2C%20she%20cannot%20be%20held%20for%20transgression%20of%20a%20parliamentary%20procedure%20and%20law.%20At%20best%2C%20she%20violated%20the%20guidelines%20which%20say%20MPs%20must%20change%20their%20passwords%20every%20three%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20crucial%20question%20is%20that%2C%20in%20the%20absence%20of%20any%20rule%20framed%20by%20parliament%20on%20the%20issue%20of%20login%20ID%20and%20password%20sharing%2C%20how%20can%20Moitra%20be%20proceeded%20against%20for%20a%20breach%20of%20the%20guidelines%3F%20The%20Lok%20Sabha%20should%20not%20encroach%20upon%20the%20domain%20of%20the%20executive.%20At%20best%2C%20the%20ethics%20committee%20of%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20should%20have%20asked%20the%20relevant%20government%20department%20to%20deal%20with%20the%20issue%20of%20Moitra%20sharing%20her%20login%20and%20password.%20The%20possible%20danger%20to%20national%20security%20and%20hacking%20of%20the%20MP%20portal%20because%20of%20sharing%20her%20login%20and%20password%20has%20been%20raised%20in%20the%20ethics%20committee%20report.%20It%20only%20refers%20to%20a%20possibility%20and%20not%20an%20actual%20eventuality.%20Based%20on%20a%20probabilistic%20scenario%2C%20the%20extreme%20measure%20of%20expelling%20Moitra%20sounds%20quite%20disproportionate.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EMoitra%20not%20allowed%20to%20speak%20in%20the%20House%20in%20her%20defence%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20ethics%20committee%20report%20on%20the%20Moitra%20issue%2C%20containing%20almost%20500%20pages%2C%20was%20made%20available%20to%20MPs%20a%20short%20while%20before%20it%20was%20taken%20up%20for%20discussion.%20As%20a%20result%20they%20could%20not%20read%20it%20and%20adequately%20apply%20their%20minds%20to%20its%20contents%20to%20deal%20with%20a%20grave%20issue%20of%20expulsion%20of%20a%20fellow%20MP.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20crucial%20point%20is%20whether%20Moitra%20got%20a%20chance%20to%20reply%20when%20the%20House%20was%20discussing%20the%20report%20to%20expel%20her.%20Clearly%20her%20request%20in%20this%20respect%20was%20not%20granted%20even%20as%20several%20other%20MPs%20participated%20in%20the%20discussion.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPrinciples%20of%20natural%20justice%20demand%20that%20the%20accused%20is%20heard%20before%20any%20decision%20is%20taken%20against%20them.%20Apparently%2C%20Lok%20Sabha%20Speaker%20Om%20Birla%20did%20not%20allow%20her%20to%20speak%20by%20citing%20the%20precedent%20of%202005%20when%20the%20aforementioned%20accused%20MPs%20were%20not%20given%20a%20chance%20to%20speak%20in%20the%20House%20by%20then%20speaker%2C%20Somnath%20Chatterjee.%20Pleadings%20of%20several%20Lok%20Sabha%20MPs%20that%20in%20the%202005%20case%20there%20was%20proven%20evidence%20against%20those%20MPs%20receiving%20cash%20and%20there%20is%20nothing%20against%20Moitra%20was%20not%20accepted%20by%20Birla.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMost%20importantly%2C%20Mohua%E2%80%99s%20expulsion%20from%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20has%20deprived%20lakhs%20of%20her%20constituents%20who%20elected%20her%20of%20their%20right%20to%20be%20represented%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha.%20This%20was%20the%20reasoning%20employed%20by%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20while%20restoring%20Rahul%20Gandhi%E2%80%99s%20Lok%20Sabha%20membership%20after%20he%20was%20disqualified%20from%20the%20House.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20has%20held%20that%20the%20disqualification%20of%20an%20MP%20adversely%20affects%20the%20rights%20of%20the%20constituents%20they%20represent%20and%20the%20right%20of%20the%20MP%20to%20represent%20those%20who%20elected%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20aforementioned%20grounds%20and%20specifically%20the%20last%20one%20raises%20the%20question%20if%20Moitra%E2%80%99s%20expulsion%20from%20a%20law%20making%20body%20is%20consistent%20with%20the%20law.%20Reflection%20on%20these%20issues%20entails%20the%20intent%20to%20uphold%20the%20dignity%2C%20privilege%20and%20fairness%20associated%20with%20the%20apex%20legislature.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ES.N.%20Sahu%20served%20as%20Officer%20on%20Special%20Duty%20to%20President%20of%20India%20K.R.%20Narayanan.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702298746000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F11163835%2FScreenshot-2023-12-11-at-4.37.14-PM.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fdid-the-lok-sabha-follow-due-process-while-expelling-mahua-moitra-from-the-house%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20ethics%20committee%20had%20no%20conclusive%20evidence%20of%20a%20cash%20trail%20leading%20to%20Mitra.%20Yet%20she%20was%20not%20given%20a%20chance%20to%20respond%20to%20the%20allegations.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A20%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fdid-the-lok-sabha-follow-due-process-while-expelling-mahua-moitra-from-the-house%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22After%20RBI%20and%20Barclay's%20Alarms%20on%20Rising%20Inflation%2C%20FM%20Says%20Retail%20Inflation%20Now%20%E2%80%98Stable%E2%80%99%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F06%2F13202718%2F5656236470_75863261e6_b.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%3Cspan%3E%20Union%20minister%20for%20finance%20Nirmala%20Sitharaman%20informed%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20on%20Monday%20(December%2011)%20that%20India%E2%80%99s%20retail%20inflation%20is%20now%20stable%20and%20within%20the%20Reserve%20Bank%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20(RBI)%20tolerance%20band%20of%202%25%20to%206%25.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESitharaman%E2%80%99s%20statement%20came%20in%20response%20to%20a%20starred%20question%20by%20Aam%20Aadmi%20Party%20MP%20Sushil%20Kumar%20Rinku%20about%20whether%20the%20Union%20government%20has%20%E2%80%9Ctaken%20note%E2%80%9D%20that%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20retail%20inflation%20is%20%E2%80%9Cincreasing%20steeply%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CIndia%E2%80%99s%20retail%20inflation%20has%20declined%20from%20an%20average%20of%207.1%25%20in%20April-October%202022%20to%205.4%25%20in%20the%20corresponding%20period%20of%202023%2C%E2%80%9D%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsansad.in%2FgetFile%2Floksabhaquestions%2Fannex%2F1714%2FAS101.pdf%3Fsource%3Dpqals%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3ESitharaman%20said%20in%20her%20written%20reply%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20retail%20inflation%20is%20now%20stable%20and%20within%20the%20notified%20tolerance%20band%20of%202%25%20to%206%25.%20A%20steady%20decline%20in%20core%20inflation%2C%20estimated%20after%20removing%20volatile%20food%20and%20fuel%20items%20from%20retail%20inflation%2C%20has%20been%20critical%20in%20weakening%20the%20inflationary%20pressure%20in%20the%20Indian%20economy.%20The%20core%20inflation%20has%20declined%20from%205.1%25%20in%20April%202023%20to%204.3%25%20in%20October%202023.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESitharaman%20added%20that%20%E2%80%9Ctemporary%20increases%20in%20inflation%20on%20a%20few%20occasions%20are%20caused%20by%20demand-supply%20mismatches%20arising%20out%20of%20global%20shocks%20and%20adverse%20weather%20conditions.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EShe%20said%20that%20proactive%20supply-side%20initiatives%20by%20the%20government%20and%20effective%20demand%20stabilisation%20measures%20by%20the%20RBI%20have%20helped%20resolve%20the%20demand-supply%20mismatches%20and%20to%20rein%20in%20inflation.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESitharaman%E2%80%99s%20statement%20comes%20after%20Barclay%E2%80%99s%20estimated%20last%20week%20that%20India%E2%80%99s%20retail%20inflation%20may%20have%20crossed%20the%20RBI%E2%80%99s%20tolerance%20limit%20of%206%25%20in%20November%20from%204.87%25%20in%20October%2C%20reported%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livemint.com%2Feconomy%2Findia-cpi-inflation-may-breach-rbis-6-tolerance-band-in-november-says-barclays-11701846767401.html%5C%22%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EMint%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20July%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20retail%20inflation%20rate%20jumped%20to%207.44%25%20%E2%80%93%20a%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Funcategorised%2Fat-15-month-high-retail-inflation-in-july-jumped-to-7-44-owing-to-soaring-vegetable-prices%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E15-month%20high%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20due%20to%20a%20massive%20surge%20in%20vegetable%20prices%2C%20data%20by%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Statistics%20and%20Programme%20Implementation%20showed.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20data%20showed%20that%20retail%20inflation%20easily%20breached%20the%20upper%20limit%20of%20the%20RBI%E2%80%99s%20tolerance%20band%20of%202%25%20to%206%25%20for%20the%20first%20time%20in%20five%20months.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOn%20Friday%2C%20RBI%20governor%20Shaktikanta%20Das%20said%20that%20high-frequency%20food%20price%20indicators%20%E2%80%9Cpoint%20to%20an%20increase%20in%20prices%20of%20key%20vegetables%20which%20may%20push%20retail%20inflation%20higher%20in%20the%20near-term%2C%E2%80%9D%20reported%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fbusiness%2Fhigh-vegetable-prices-may-push-up-retail-inflation-in-near-term-rbi-governor-9060481%2F%5C%22%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Indian%20Express%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20near-term%20outlook%20is%20masked%20by%20risks%20to%20food%20inflation%2C%20which%20might%20lead%20to%20an%20inflation%20uptick%20in%20November%20and%20December%2C%E2%80%9D%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fbusiness%2Fhigh-vegetable-prices-may-push-up-retail-inflation-in-near-term-rbi-governor-9060481%2F%5C%22%3EDas%20said%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20adding%20that%20%E2%80%9Cfood%20inflation%20is%20going%20to%20increase%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHe%20said%20that%20%E2%80%9Csignificant%20progress%E2%80%9D%20has%20been%20made%20in%20bringing%20down%20inflation%20to%20below%205%25%20in%20October.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EDas%20said%20that%20retail%20inflation%20is%20projected%20at%205.4%25%20for%202023-24.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESitharaman%20said%20that%20the%20measures%20taken%20by%20the%20government%20to%20restrain%20inflation%20include%20the%20strengthening%20of%20buffers%20of%20key%20food%20items%20and%20making%20periodic%20open%20market%20releases%2C%20easing%20imports%20of%20essential%20food%20items%20through%20trade%20policy%20measures%2C%20preventing%20hoarding%20through%20the%20imposition%2Frevision%20of%20stock%20limits%2C%20and%20channelling%20supplies%20through%20designated%20retail%20outlets.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EShe%20added%20that%20to%20ensure%20food%20security%20to%20the%20poor%2C%20the%20Pradhan%20Mantri%20Garib%20Kalyan%20Anna%20Yojana%20that%20provides%20free%20food%20grains%20to%20about%2081.35%20crore%20beneficiaries%2C%20has%20been%20extended%20for%20a%20period%20of%20five%20years%20with%20effect%20from%20January%201%2C%202024.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EShe%20also%20cited%20that%20in%20October%2C%20the%20Union%20government%20also%20increased%20the%20subsidy%20under%20the%20Pradhan%20Mantri%20Ujjwala%20Yojana%20from%20Rs%20200%20to%20Rs%20300%20per%2014.2%20kg%20cylinder.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20August%2C%20the%20Narendra%20Modi%20government%20reduced%20the%20price%20of%20LPG%20cylinders%20by%20Rs%20200%20and%20pegged%20it%20as%20a%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Flpg-price-cut-modis-rakhi-gift-ends-up-drawing-attention-to-inflation%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CRakhi%20gift%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20to%20the%20women%20of%2