as%20raised%20questions%20about%20aggressive%20mind%20management%20and%20media%20manipulation%20in%20Indian%20elections.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20perception%2C%20however%2C%20is%20not%20solely%20attributed%20to%20Electronic%20Voting%20Machine%20(EVM)%20doubts%20but%20also%20underscores%20deeper%20issues%20within%20India%E2%80%99s%20flawed%20electoral%20system%2C%20particularly%20the%20First%20Past%20the%20Post%20(FPTP)%20system.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Findia-elections-first-past-the-post%5C%22%3EDoes%20the%20First-Past-The-Post%20System%20Still%20Make%20Sense%20for%20India%3F%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EFirst%20Past%20the%20Post%20system%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Congress%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thequint.com%2Fnews%2Fpolitics%2Fcongress-bjp-votes-chhatisgarh-mizoram-mp-rajasthan-telangana-election-results%23read-more%5C%22%3Ereceived%3C%2Fa%3E%2010%2C55%2C033%20more%20votes%20than%20the%20BJP.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20these%20five%20states%2C%20the%20BJP%20won%20342%20seats%2C%20and%20the%20Congress%20won%20only%20235%2C%20a%20difference%20of%20107%20seats.%20This%20means%20that%20despite%20securing%20over%2010.5%20lakh%20more%20votes%20than%20the%20BJP%20in%20these%20states%2C%20the%20Congress%20lost%20in%20three%20of%20them%2C%20raising%20serious%20concerns%20about%20the%20fairness%20of%20the%20election%20process.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20Rajasthan%20and%20Chhattisgarh%2C%20the%20Congress%20lost%20mainly%20because%20of%20a%20five-year%20anti-incumbency%20factor.%20In%20Madhya%20Pradesh%2C%20the%20BJP%20won%20hugely%20by%20a%20margin%20of%207.6%25%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.deccanherald.com%2Felections%2Fmadhya-pradesh%2Fgain-of-over-7-in-vote-share-powers-bjp-to-sweep-mp-2795637%5C%22%3Evote%20share%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20despite%20ruling%20the%20state%20for%20the%20last%2018%20years.%20This%20scenario%20seems%20bizarre%20because%20in%20the%202018%20election%2C%20the%20BJP%20had%20lost%20to%20Congress%20by%20a%204%25%20vote%20margin%20due%20to%20the%20anti-incumbency%20factor.%20In%20fact%2C%20it%20had%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fassembly-election-rsults-why-bjp-lost-chhattisgarh%5C%22%3Eengineer%3C%2Fa%3E%20huge%20defection%20to%20re-capture%20power.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDoes%20this%20imply%20that%20the%20MP%20voters%20are%20inherently%20different%20from%20their%20neighbours%2C%20and%20have%20generously%20rewarded%20the%20rot%20of%20incumbency%20and%20crass%20defections%2C%20as%20well%20as%20the%20trading%20of%20MLAs%3F%20Such%20a%20notion%20is%20challenging%20to%20accept.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELet%E2%80%99s%20look%20at%20what%20happened%20in%20the%202019%20parliament%20election%20with%20a%20total%20electorate%20of%2091.05%20crore%2C%20out%20of%20which%2067.4%25%20were%20polled%2C%20amounting%20to%2061.36%20crore%20voters.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20ruling%20BJP%20secured%2037.36%25%20of%20these%20polled%20votes%2C%20which%20amounted%20to%2022.90%20crore%20voters%20and%20303%20seats.%20Had%20it%20been%20a%20proportional%20representation%20system%2C%20instead%20of%20the%20archaic%20and%20highly%20flawed%20first-past-the-post%20system%20(or%20the%20simple%20majority%20system%2C%20wherein%20the%20candidate%20with%20the%20highest%20number%20of%20votes%20in%20a%20constituency%20is%20declared%20the%20winner)%20as%20it%20is%20now%2C%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20seat%20share%20would%20have%20been%20only%20201%20in%20a%20House%20of%20542.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20party%E2%80%99s%20vote%20share%20as%20percentage%20of%20the%20total%20electorate%20was%20just%2025.15%25%2C%20which%20meant%20that%20the%20present%20Union%20government%20that%20is%20turning%20the%20constitution%20and%20institutions%20of%20democratic%20governance%20upside%20down%2C%20represents%20only%20one-fourth%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20electorate.%20Yet%2C%20we%20call%20our%20country%20a%20%E2%80%98representative%20democracy%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20election%2C%20the%20Association%20for%20Democratic%20Reforms%20and%20Common%20Cause%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livelaw.in%2Ftop-stories%2Fdiscrepancies-in-17th-lok-sabha-election-results--150779%5C%22%3Emoved%20the%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20challenging%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20validity%20of%20the%20low%20mandate%2C%20alleging%20that%20there%20had%20been%20serious%20discrepancies%20between%20the%20number%20of%20voters%20in%20different%20constituencies%20and%20the%20number%20of%20votes%20counted.%20These%20discrepancies%2C%20totalling%20739%2C104%20votes%2C%20were%20in%20347%20out%20of%20542%20constituencies%20and%20range%20from%20one%20vote%20to%20101%2C323%20votes%2C%20amounting%20to%2010.49%25%20of%20the%20total%20votes.%20The%20case%20has%20not%20even%20been%20listed%20so%20far%2C%20and%20there%20has%20been%20no%20response%20from%20the%20Election%20Commission%20(EC)%20on%20the%20allegation%20of%20fraud%20in%20India%E2%80%99s%20electoral%20system.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20EC%E2%80%99s%20conduct%20of%20the%202019%20general%20election%20and%20its%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Felection-commission-bjp-polls-fairness-citizens-commission-on-elections-report%5C%22%3Efairness%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fscroll.in%2Flatest%2F929251%2Fex-civil-servants-claim-2019-elections-appear-to-have-been-one-of-the-least-free-and-fair%5C%22%3Ewas%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fashoka-university-facultys-research-paper-on-bjp-manipulation-in-2019-election-triggers-row%5C%22%3Ecriticised%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Felections-2019-among-least-free-and-fair-in-three-decades-ex-officials-write-to-ec%5C%22%3Eby%20several%20experts%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20including%20academicians%2C%20civil%20society%20organisations%2C%20political%20parties%2C%20and%20former%20bureaucrats.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20EC%E2%80%99s%20reaction%20to%20these%20significant%20public%20concerns%20exhibited%20an%20indifference%20bordering%20on%20hostility.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Felection-commissioners-appointment-bill-farewell-to-free-and-fair-elections%5C%22%3EElection%20Commissioners%E2%80%99%20Appointment%20Bill%3A%20Farewell%20to%20Free%20and%20Fair%20Elections%3F%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202021%2C%20the%20Citizens%E2%80%99%20Commission%20on%20Elections%20(CCE)%2C%20headed%20by%20a%20former%20Supreme%20Court%20Judge%2C%20released%20its%20second%20report%2C%20analysing%20the%20critical%20aspects%20concerning%20elections.%20It%20was%20formed%20to%20seek%20expert%20advice%20on%20elections%20and%20generate%20appropriate%20findings%20and%20provide%20suggestions%20to%20ensure%20the%20conduct%20of%20elections%20with%20fairness%20and%20integrity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20EVM%20issue%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDuring%20this%20process%2C%20six%20themes%20were%20identified%20and%20dealt%20with%20in%20depth.%20On%20the%20EVM%20(electronic%20voting%20machine)%20issue%2C%20the%20Commission%20had%20depositions%20from%20the%20best%20of%20national%20and%20international%20experts.%20These%20are%20the%20main%20findings%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIntegrity%20and%20inclusiveness%20of%20the%20electoral%20rolls%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFirstly%2C%20significant%20exclusion%2Fdeletions%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.epw.in%2Fengage%2Farticle%2Felectoral-exclusion-muslims-continues-plague-indian-democracy%5C%22%3Ehave%20been%20noticed%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20vulnerable%2C%20disadvantaged%20groups%20and%20minority%20communities%2C%20such%20as%20Muslims%20and%20Christians.%20The%20electoral%20rolls%20registration%20machinery%20has%20been%20found%20deficient%20in%20carrying%20out%20a%20door-to-door%20enrolment%20campaign.%20Verification%20of%20names%20in%20the%20voter%E2%80%99s%20list%20has%20become%20a%20difficult%20task.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESecond%2C%20the%20migrant%20population%20has%20a%20major%20problem%20of%20casting%20their%20votes%20at%20the%20polling%20station.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThird%2C%20it%20is%20important%20to%20ensure%20that%20the%20maintenance%20of%20records%20should%20enable%20complete%20and%20public%20verifiability.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20above%20are%20necessary%20conditions%20for%20ensuring%20the%20integrity%20of%20the%20electoral%20rolls.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESeparately%2C%20EC%E2%80%99s%20action%20to%20link%20voter%20ID%20with%20Aadhaar%20is%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fdangerous-move-over-500-individuals-orgs-decry-ec-proposal-to-link-aadhaar-voter-id%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98very%20dangerous%20proposition%E2%80%99%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20could%20lead%20to%20massive%20data%20leak%2C%20fraud%2C%20and%20theft%20that%20can%20severely%20endanger%20India%E2%80%99s%20democracy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EElectronic%20voting%20%5BEVM%2FVVPATs%5D%20and%20its%20compliance%20with%20democracy%20principles%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEVM%20voting%20does%20not%20comply%20with%20the%20essential%20requirements%20of%20%E2%80%98democracy%20principles%E2%80%99%2C%20i.e.%2C%20each%20voter%20having%20the%20direct%20knowledge%20and%20capacity%20to%20verify%20that%20their%20vote%20is%20cast%20as%20intended%2C%20recorded%20as%20cast%2C%20and%20counted%20as%20recorded.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20also%20does%20not%20provide%20provable%20guarantees%20against%20hacking%2C%20tampering%2C%20and%20spurious%20vote%20injections.%20Thus%2C%20elections%20must%20be%20conducted%20assuming%20that%20the%20EVMs%20may%20possibly%20be%20tampered%20with.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThough%20VVPAT%20is%20installed%20in%20every%20EVM%2C%20not%20even%20one%20paper%20slip%20is%20counted%20and%20matched%20to%20verify%20or%20audit%20the%20votes%20polled%20and%20votes%20counted%20before%20making%20the%20results%20public.%20This%20has%20exposed%20elections%20to%20serious%20fraud.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20design%20and%20implementation%20of%20ECI-EVMs%2C%20as%20well%20as%20the%20results%20of%20both%20software%20and%20hardware%20verification%2C%20are%20not%20made%20public.%20They%20have%20also%20not%20been%20opened%20to%20full%20independent%20review.%20The%20VVPAT%20system%20does%20not%20allow%20the%20voter%20to%20verify%20the%20slip%20before%20the%20vote%20is%20cast.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDue%20to%20absence%20of%20end-to-end%20(E2E)%20verifiability%2C%20the%20present%20EVM%20system%20is%20not%20verifiable%2C%20and%20therefore%20is%20unfit%20for%20democratic%20elections.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20a%20stringent%20pre-audit%20of%20the%20electronic%20vote%20count%20must%20be%20conducted%20before%20the%20results%20are%20declared.%20This%20may%20require%20a%20full%20manual%20counting%20of%20the%20VVPAT%20slips.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20electronic%20voting%20system%20should%20be%20redesigned%20to%20be%20software%20and%20hardware%20independent%2C%20in%20order%20to%20be%20verifiable%20or%20auditable.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECriminalisation%2C%20money%20power%2C%20and%20electoral%20bonds%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20are%20enormous%20problems.%20The%20proportion%20of%20winning%20candidates%20with%20a%20criminal%20background%20paints%20a%20very%20grim%20picture.%20MPs%20with%20serious%20criminal%20cases%20against%20them%20constituted%2014%25%20in%202009%2C%2021%25%20in%202014%2C%20and%2029%25%20in%202019.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20least%20162%20MPs%20declared%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Findia%2Falmost-half-of-newly-elected-mps-have-criminal-cases-against-them-adr%2Farticleshow%2F69508179.cms%5C%22%3Ecriminal%20cases%3C%2Fa%3E%20against%20them%20in%202009%2C%20which%20increased%20to%20185%20in%202014%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hindustantimes.com%2Flok-sabha-elections%2Fnew-lok-sabha-sees-9-rise-in-number-of-mps-with-criminal-charges%2Fstory-miRruaSzo6EEC0XcVSbUJJ.html%5C%22%3E233%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202019.%20Those%20with%20serious%20declared%20criminal%20offenses%20increased%20from%2076%20in%202009%20to%20112%20in%202014%2C%20and%20to%20159%20in%202019.%20The%20trend%20is%20evidently%20on%20the%20rise.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMoney%20and%20power%20in%20elections%20serve%20as%20the%20fountainhead%20of%20corruption%20in%20the%20country.%20It%20compromises%20the%20integrity%20of%20democracy%20in%20multiple%20ways%2C%20such%20as%20by%20raising%20entry%20barriers%20to%20politics%2C%20excluding%20honest%20candidates%20and%20parties%2C%20allowing%20big%20money%20to%20control%20the%20state%2C%20and%20leading%20to%20distortions%20in%20policymaking.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EElectoral%20bonds%20have%20increased%20opaqueness%20and%20consolidated%20the%20role%20of%20big%20money%20in%20electoral%20politics%2C%20giving%20huge%20advantage%20to%20the%20ruling%20party%20and%20destroying%20a%20level-playing%20field.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.news18.com%2Fnews%2Fpolitics%2Fwith-about-rs-100-cr-spent-in-each-ls-constituency-we-just-witnessed-the-most-expensive-election-ever-2171789.html%5C%22%3ECentre%20for%20Media%20Studies%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20total%20expenditure%20on%20the%202019%20parliament%20election%20was%20estimated%20at%20a%20staggering%20Rs%2060%2C000%20crore.%20The%20ruling%20BJP%20reportedly%20spent%20close%20to%20Rs%2027%2C000%20crore%2C%20i.e.%20Rs%2089%20crore%20per%20seat.%20It%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Findia%2Flok-sabha-election-2019-results-bjp-won-303-seats-was-main-contender-in-another-72-5747525%2F%5C%22%3Ewon%3C%2Fa%3E%20303%20seats.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20fast-rising%20economic%20oligarchy%20in%20the%20country%2C%20threatening%20India%20as%20a%20welfare%20state%2C%20is%20the%20direct%20fallout%20of%20this%20extreme%20criminal%20and%20money%20power%20in%20elections.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EScheduling%20and%20processes%20of%20elections%20and%20compliance%20of%20Model%20Code%20of%20Conduct%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20the%202019%20parliament%20election%2C%20the%20EC%2C%20per%20civil%20servants%20and%20military%20veterans%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fclarionindia.net%2Fcivil-servants-military-veterans-question-silence-inaction-of-ec-on-lok-sabha-election-issues%2F%5C%22%3Edeliberately%20delayed%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20announcement%20to%20enable%20the%20prime%20minister%20to%20complete%20the%20inauguration%20blitz%20of%20a%20slew%20of%20projects%20(157%20of%20them)%20that%20he%20had%20scheduled%20between%20February%208%20and%20March%209.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20the%20longest%20election%20in%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20history%2C%20and%20its%20scheduling%20gave%20room%20for%20suspicion%20that%20it%20had%20openly%20and%20unabashedly%20favoured%20the%20ruling%20party%2C%20they%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESome%20major%20controversies%20surrounding%20the%20Model%20Code%20of%20Conduct%20include%20a%20lack%20of%20consistency%20by%20the%20EC%20in%20enforcing%20it%2C%20treating%20the%20ruling%20party%20with%20kid%20gloves%2C%20and%20not%20utilising%20its%20powers%20under%20Article%20324%20of%20the%20Constitution.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Election%20Commissioner%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Felection-commissioner-ashok-lavasa-known-for-dissent-in-ec-may-leave-early-for-adb-job%5C%22%3EAshok%20Lavasa%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20who%20was%20known%20for%20dissent%20in%20EC%2C%20was%20unceremoniously%20removed%20and%20was%20denied%20the%20opportunity%20to%20become%20Chief%20Election%20Commissioner.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Model%20Code%20of%20Conduct%E2%80%99s%20%3Cspan%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eraison%20d%E2%80%99etre%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fspan%3Ewas%20to%20provide%20a%20level-playing%20field%20to%20all%20contesting%20political%20parties.%20Dealing%20with%20the%20ruling%20party%20with%20kid%20gloves%20negates%20the%20very%20reason%20for%20its%20existence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAdditionally%2C%20the%20use%20(misuse%2Fabuse)%20of%20armed%20forces%C2%A0%20for%20election%20purposes%20by%20the%20party%20in%20power%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.newsclick.in%2Farmed-forces-veterans-letter-president-india-election-commission%5C%22%3Ewas%20severely%20criticised%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20retired%20soldiers%2C%20sailors%2C%20and%20airmen.%20Calling%20the%20Indian%20Army%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Felections%2Fyogi-adityanath-indian-army-opposition-pm-modi-ji-ke-sena-5653158%2F%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98Modiji%20ki%20Sena%E2%80%99%3C%2Fa%3E%20resulted%20in%20strong%20protests%20from%20veterans%20and%20opposition%20parties.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fmodi-magic-is-nothing-but-bjp-pr-amplified-by-media%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98Modi%20Magic%E2%80%99%20Is%20Nothing%20but%20BJP%20PR%20Amplified%20by%20Media%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20role%20of%20media%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20very%20substantial%20section%20of%20the%20mainstream%20and%20mass%20media%20in%20the%20country%20has%20become%20excessively%20supportive%20of%20the%20ruling%20BJP.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDespite%20guidelines%20and%20codes%2C%20the%20EC%20did%20not%20take%20note%20of%20the%20many%20media%20violations%2C%20particularly%20by%20the%20ruling%20party.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20new%20channel%20called%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fmedia%2Fas-polls-draw-to-a-close-namo-tv-slips-off-air%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98Namo%20TV%E2%80%99%3C%2Fa%3E%20cropped%20up%20in%20March%202019%20without%20any%20licence%20or%20permission.%20It%20went%20on%20air%20and%20did%20full-time%20propaganda%20for%20the%20ruling%20party.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20EC%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.newsclick.in%2FElection-Commission-India-Failed-Curb-Fake-News-Lok-Sabha-2019%5C%22%3Efailed%20to%20curb%20fake%20news%3C%2Fa%3E%20online%20before%20and%20during%20the%202019%20elections.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EEC%E2%80%99s%20autonomy%20and%20its%20functioning%20before%2C%20during%2C%20and%20after%20elections%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20EC%20has%20plenipotentiary%20powers%20drawn%20from%20Article%20324%20of%20the%20Constitution%20of%20India%20to%20conduct%20free%20and%20fair%20elections.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20has%20ruled%3A%20%E2%80%9CWhen%20Parliament%20or%20any%20State%20Legislature%20made%20valid%20law%20relating%20to%2C%20or%20in%20connection%20with%20elections%2C%20the%20Commission%2C%20shall%20act%20in%20conformity%20with%2C%20not%20in%20violation%20of%2C%20such%20provisions%2C%20but%20where%20such%20law%20is%20silent%2C%20Article%20324%20is%20a%20reservoir%20of%20power%20to%20act%20for%20the%20avowed%20purpose%20of%20pushing%20forward%20a%20free%20and%20fair%20election%20with%20expedition%E2%80%A6%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20EC%20is%20just%20not%20using%20these%20powers%2C%20because%20Commissioners%20are%20the%20appointees%20of%20the%20Government%20of%20the%20day%20and%20not%20through%20an%20independent%20process%20of%20collegium.%20This%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Freclaimtherepublic.in%2Fcategory%2Freport%2Fcce-report%2F%5C%22%3Ecompromises%20the%20autonomy%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20the%20EC%20and%20creates%20doubts%20about%20the%20neutrality%20of%20the%20Chief%20Election%20Commissioner%20and%20the%20Election%20Commissioners%2C%20and%20consequently%2C%20the%20neutrality%20of%20the%20Commission%20itself.%20This%20poses%20serious%20danger%20to%20the%20fairness%20and%20integrity%20of%20not%20only%20the%20elections%2C%20but%20democracy%20itself.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20EC%20has%20been%20blind%2C%20deaf%2C%20and%20dumb%20on%20this%20objective%20analysis%20and%20report%2C%20as%20well%20as%20subsequent%20pleadings.%20In%20the%20event%2C%20things%20have%20been%20going%20from%20bad%20to%20worse%20and%20there%20are%20serious%20doubts%20as%20to%20whether%20India%E2%80%99s%20elections%20are%20free%20and%20fair.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20in%20this%20context%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20exultant%20prediction%20of%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fbjp-assembly-elections-hat-trick-2024%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98hat-trick%20in%202024%E2%80%99%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20to%20be%20viewed.%20Is%20it%20going%20to%20be%20%3Cem%3Erequiem%3C%2Fem%3E%20for%20India%E2%80%99s%20electoral%20democracy%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fauthor%2Fm-g-devasahayam-2%5C%22%3EM.G.%20Devasahayam%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20a%20former%20Army%20and%20IAS%20officer.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702294242000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F01%2F16163914%2F2048px-BMC_Election_2012_-_Ink_mark_after_voting_6886404209.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fare-indias-elections-free-and-fair%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20BJP%20secured%20victories%20in%20three%20states%20and%20the%20Congress%20in%20one.%20However%2C%20the%20Congress%20garnered%20more%20votes%20than%20the%20BJP.%20A%20critical%20examination%20of%20the%20electoral%20landscape%20reveals%20intriguing%20disparities.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A3%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fare-indias-elections-free-and-fair%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22'Sad%20But%20Not%20Unexpected%3A%20J%26amp%3BK%20Political%20Parties%20React%20to%20SC%20Verdict%20on%20Article%20370%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F11163902%2Fomar-mehbooba.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20verdict%20on%20J%26amp%3BK%E2%80%99s%20constitutional%20relationship%20with%20the%20Union%20of%20India%20evoked%20a%20subdued%20response%20in%20the%20union%20territory%20on%20Monday%2C%20December%2011%2C%20where%20the%20BJP-led%20Union%20government%E2%80%99s%20move%20in%202019%20was%20largely%20treated%20as%20%3Cem%3Efait%20accompli%3C%2Fem%3E%20and%20its%20approval%20by%20the%20judiciary%20as%20a%20mere%20formality.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CRather%20than%20our%20loss%2C%E2%80%9D%20Mehbooba%20Mufti%20said%20in%20a%20video%20address%20to%20her%20party%20workers%20after%20the%20SC%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fsupreme-court-kashmir-article-370-verdict%5C%22%3Edelivered%20its%20verdict%3C%2Fa%3E%20upholding%20the%20order%20reading%20down%20Article%20370.%20%E2%80%9CIt%20is%20the%20idea%20of%20India%20which%20has%20suffered%20a%20defeat%20today.%20The%20betrayal%20has%20come%20from%20them%2C%20not%20us.%20By%20terming%20Article%20370%20as%20a%20%E2%80%98temporary%E2%80%99%20provision%2C%20the%20country%20has%20been%20weakened%20while%20those%20powers%20who%20termed%20J%26amp%3BK%E2%80%99s%20accession%20with%20India%20as%20%E2%80%98temporary%E2%80%99%20have%20got%20strengthened.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlleging%20that%20she%20was%20put%20under%20house%20arrest%20on%20Monday%2C%20Mehbooba%20added%3A%20%E2%80%9CThe%20illegal%20decision%20of%20the%20Union%20government%20in%20the%20parliament%20(on%20August%205%2C%202019)%20and%20the%20legal%20approval%20granted%20by%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20is%20no%20less%20than%20a%20death%20punishment%20for%20the%20idea%20of%20India.%20But%20we%20will%20continue%20to%20fight%20peacefully%20for%20our%20rights%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMehbooba%2C%20who%20heads%20the%20Peoples%20Democratic%20Party%20(PDP)%2C%20was%20among%20three%20former%20chief%20ministers%20of%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20who%20were%20taken%20into%20preventive%20custody%20in%20August%202019%2C%20ahead%20of%20the%20Union%20government%E2%80%99s%20decision%20to%20bifurcate%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20and%20downgrade%20it%20to%20union%20territory%20status.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFollowing%20the%20court%E2%80%99s%20ruling%2C%20the%20PDP%20has%20also%20suspended%20all%20political%20activities%20for%20a%20week%20%E2%80%9Cin%20solidarity%20with%20the%20people%20of%20J%26amp%3BK%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20Read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fin-jammu-and-kashmir-all-eyes-are-on-the-supreme-court-today%5C%22%3EIn%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20Verdict%2C%20the%20SC%20Has%20Done%20What%20Many%20Locals%20Had%20Feared%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20former%20J%26amp%3BK%20chief%20minister%2C%20Omar%20Abdullah%20also%20alleged%20that%20he%20was%20put%20under%20house%20arrest%20on%20Monday%20morning%20ahead%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20verdict.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20live%20broadcast%20on%20X%20(formerly%20Twitter)%2C%20Omar%20said%20that%20the%20main%20gate%20of%20his%20Srinagar%20home%20had%20been%20locked%20and%20he%20was%20prevented%20from%20speaking%20to%20the%20media.%20Media%20persons%20were%20turned%20away%20by%20authorities%2C%20he%20claimed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20knocked%20on%20the%20doors%20of%20SC%20with%20the%20hope%20of%20justice.%20I%20respect%20the%20court%E2%80%99s%20decision.%20We%20may%20have%20failed%2C%20the%20decision%20may%20be%20disappointing%2C%20but%20it%20is%20a%20temporary%20setback.%20Ours%20is%20a%20political%20fight%20and%20we%20will%20fight%20it%20within%20the%20ambit%20of%20law%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20added%3A%20%E2%80%9CThe%20BJP%20succeeded%20in%20achieving%20its%20political%20objective%20after%2070%20years.%20We%20too%20will%20continue%20to%20strive%20politically%20so%20that%20whatever%20was%20snatched%20from%20us%20on%20August%205%2C%202019%20is%20given%20back.%20Whether%20it%20is%20possible%20to%20again%20knock%20on%20the%20door%20of%20the%20court%20will%20be%20decided%20after%20our%20lawyers%20go%20into%20the%20details%20of%20the%20verdict.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EReacting%20to%20the%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20observations%20on%20the%20restoration%20of%20J%26amp%3BK%E2%80%99s%20statehood%20and%20the%20direction%20to%20the%20Union%20government%20on%20holding%20assembly%20elections%20in%20the%20union%20territory%20by%20September%20next%20year%2C%20Abdullah%20said%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CElection%20is%20not%20a%20pressing%20issue%20and%20statehood%20also%20is%20not%20an%20important%20issue%20for%20us.%20We%20were%20not%20expecting%20a%20verdict%20like%20this%20but%20maybe%20we%20will%20succeed%20next%20time.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20video%20address%2C%20J%26amp%3BK%E2%80%99s%20Lieutenant%20Governor%20Manoj%20Sinha%20rejected%20the%20%E2%80%98house%20arrest%E2%80%99%20claims%20of%20Mufti%20and%20Abdullah%2C%20terming%20them%20as%20%E2%80%9Ctotally%20baseless%E2%80%9D.%20%E2%80%9CNo%20one%20has%20been%20put%20under%20house%20arrest%20or%20arrested%20due%20to%20political%20reasons.%20It%20is%20an%20attempt%20to%20spread%20rumours%E2%80%9D%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPolice%20in%20Srinagar%20district%2C%20which%20is%20home%20to%20Kashmir%E2%80%99s%20top%20political%20leadership%2C%20also%20claimed%20that%20no%20one%20was%20under%20house%20arrest.%20However%2C%20media%20persons%20were%20turned%20away%20from%20Gupkar%20Road%2C%20where%20Abdullah%20lives%20along%20with%20his%20father%20and%20Lok%20Sabha%20MP%20Farooq%20Abdullah.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F07%2F30042256%2FScreenshot-2020-07-30-at-4.20.52-AM.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221073%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F07%2F30042256%2FScreenshot-2020-07-30-at-4.20.52-AM.png%201073w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fc