rs.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIsrael%E2%80%99s%20brutal%20and%20massively%20disproportionate%20retaliation%20to%20Hamas%E2%80%99%20murderous%20rampage%20on%20October%207%20has%20drawn%20much%20condemnation%20but%20little%20action.%20Security%20council%20vacillation%20on%20calling%20for%20a%20cease-fire%20forced%20secretary-general%20Guterres%20to%20invoke%20article%2099%20of%20the%20charter%2C%20which%20requires%20the%20security%20council%20to%20meet%20urgently%2C%20for%20the%20first%20time%20in%20four%20decades.%20But%20the%20U.S.%20vetoed%20the%20council%E2%80%99s%20resolution%20for%20an%20immediate%20cease-fire.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFormer%20prosecutors%20of%20the%20International%20Criminal%20Court%20(ICC)%2C%20which%20began%20investigating%20war%20crimes%20and%20settler%20violence%20in%202021%2C%20argue%20that%20both%20Hamas%E2%80%99%20attack%20and%20the%20Israeli%20retaliation%20can%20be%20considered%20genocide%20and%20crimes%20against%20humanity.%20But%20the%20ICC%E2%80%99s%20current%20chief%20prosecutor%2C%20Karim%20Khan%2C%20visited%20the%20Rafah%20crossing%20four%20unbearable%20weeks%20into%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20bombardment%20of%20Gaza.%20He%20visited%20Israel%20and%20the%20West%20Bank%20only%20a%20few%20days%20ago.%20He%20is%20yet%20to%20visit%20Gaza.%20Small%20wonder%20Palestinian%20human%20rights%20groups%20refused%20to%20meet%20him.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20560px)%2085vw%2C%20560px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F08150335%2Fimage560x340cropped.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22560%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F08150335%2Fimage560x340cropped.jpg%20560w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F08150335%2Fimage560x340cropped-300x182.jpg%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-688317%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22340%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EMen%20walk%20through%20the%20destroyed%20streets%20of%20Gaza.%20Photo%3A%20WHO%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ENow%2C%20while%20violence%20escalates%20with%20even%20more%20sickening%20instances%20of%20brutality%2C%20and%20the%20expulsion%20of%20Palestinians%20from%20Gaza%20and%20the%20West%20Bank%20continues%2C%20international%20policymakers%20have%20started%20talking%20about%20%E2%80%98the%20day%20after%E2%80%99.%20Israeli%20Prime%20Minister%20Benjamin%20Netanyahu%20plans%20to%20turn%20most%20of%20north%20Gaza%20into%20a%20military%20buffer%20zone%20after%20his%20war%20cabinet%20decides%20that%20Hamas%20has%20been%20destroyed%2C%20and%20refuses%20to%20check%20settler%20expansion%20in%20the%20West%20Bank.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EUS%20President%20Joe%20Biden%20and%20Vice-President%20Kamala%20Harris%20have%20opposed%20his%20plan%2C%20but%20agree%20that%20security%20for%20Gaza%20and%20the%20West%20Bank%20should%20remain%20with%20Israel%20until%20a%20lasting%20solution%20is%20found.%20But%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20security%20control%20is%20the%20root%20cause%20of%20the%20problem%2C%20which%20is%20currently%20exacerbated%20by%20Egypt%E2%80%99s%20refusal%20to%20open%20its%20borders%20to%20Gazan%20refugees.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20peace%20activist%20Avi%20Shlaim%20has%20repeatedly%20stressed%2C%20successive%20Israeli%20prime%20ministers%20used%20control%20over%20Palestinian%20security%20to%20undermine%20the%201992-1993%20Oslo%20accords%20through%20settlement%20expansion.%20They%20encountered%20little%20resistance%20from%20the%20US%2C%20UK%2C%20Europe%20or%20the%20Arab%20countries.%20Writing%20in%202011%2C%20the%20Pakistani%20columnist%20Irfan%20Husain%2C%20whose%20selected%20works%20I%20have%20been%20reading%20over%20the%20past%20few%20weeks%2C%20commented%20bitterly%20that%20Palestine%E2%80%99s%20Arab%20neighbours%20and%20the%20larger%20comity%20of%20Muslim%20countries%20had%20abandoned%20the%20Palestinians%3B%20in%20doing%20so%2C%20they%20failed%20their%20own%20people%20who%20overwhelmingly%20supported%20the%20Palestinian%20right%20to%20self-determination%20(Irfan%20Husain%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EA%20Life%20Lived%20with%20Passion%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%202023).%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fwitnessing-palestine-in-new-york-and-watching-indias-moral-vision-disappear%5C%22%3EWitnessing%20Palestine%20in%20New%20York%20%E2%80%93%20and%20Watching%20India%E2%80%99s%20Moral%20Vision%20Disappear%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20failure%20of%20the%20Oslo%20accords%20and%20the%20fragmentation%20of%20the%20West%20Bank%20into%20isolated%20hamlets%20under%20constant%20threat%20from%20settlers%20is%20clear%20indication%20that%20an%20incremental%20process%20will%20not%20work.%20It%20may%20be%20that%20an%20interim%20arrangement%20is%20necessary%20to%20allow%20cooling-off%20before%20political%20negotiations%20for%20a%20lasting%20solution%20begin.%20If%20so%2C%20security%20will%20need%20to%20be%20in%20the%20hands%20of%20an%20international%20peace-keeping%20force.%20The%20Netanyahu%20administration%20will%20be%20extremely%20reluctant%20to%20accept%20such%20a%20force%2C%20but%20the%20US%20has%20sufficient%20power%20to%20pressure%20it%20into%20agreement.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhat%20could%20a%20lasting%20solution%20comprise%3F%20Most%20countries%20favour%20a%20two-state%20solution%20based%20on%20the%201967%20borders%2C%20which%20the%20bulk%20of%20policy%20analysts%20suggest%20is%20dead%3B%20some%20peace%20advocates%20suggest%20a%20binational%20state.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EPartition%20has%20rarely%20been%20a%20desired%20outcome%2C%20even%20in%20countries%20that%20acceded%20to%20it%2C%20and%20it%20has%20had%20mixed%20results%20as%20the%20least%20bad%20solution%2C%20often%20resulting%20in%20entrenching%20rather%20than%20overcoming%20hostility.%20Given%20that%20it%20appears%20to%20be%20the%20only%20feasible%20solution%2C%20however%2C%20are%20there%20any%20lessons%20on%20how%20to%20minimise%20its%20negative%20outcomes%3F%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%98What%20if%E2%80%99%20analyses%20are%20rare%20in%20South%20Asia%2C%20but%20Irfan%20found%20that%20one%20plus%20of%20partition%20was%20that%20it%20had%20benefited%20Pakistan%20economically.%20The%20flow%20of%20Muslim%20elites%20from%20India%20brought%20intellectual%20and%20technical%20expertise%20which%20combined%20with%20liberal%20economic%20policies%20to%20develop%20what%20had%20earlier%20been%20underdeveloped%20areas.%20A%20similar%20inflow%20might%20well%20occur%20in%20the%20Palestinian%20territories%20if%20the%20occupation%20ends%2C%20with%20the%20benefit%20of%20stability%20for%20Israel.%20But%20much%20will%20depend%20on%20whether%20Israel%20will%20resume%20employment%20of%20labor%20from%20Gaza%20and%20the%20West%20Bank%2C%20whose%20wages%20make%20up%20close%20to%20a%20quarter%20of%20both%20economies.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F16120732%2Fimage1170x530cropped-5.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221170%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F16120732%2Fimage1170x530cropped-5.jpg%201170w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F16120732%2Fimage1170x530cropped-5-300x136.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F16120732%2Fimage1170x530cropped-5-1024x464.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-685017%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22530%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ELarge%20areas%20of%20the%20Gaza%20Strip%20have%20been%20destroyed%20by%20missile%20strikes.%20Photo%3A%20WHO%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20India-Pakistan%20negatives%20are%20more%20numerous.%20Pakistan%20%E2%80%93%20as%20Reginald%20Copeland%20foresaw%20in%20the%201940s%20%E2%80%93%20invested%20ruinous%20amounts%20in%20security%2C%20a%20problem%20that%20might%20not%20occur%20in%20the%20Israeli%20or%20Palestinian%20case%2C%20since%20the%20former%20will%20save%20by%20ending%20the%20occupation%20and%20the%20latter%20will%20most%20likely%20depend%20on%20neighbour%20or%20international%20security%20guarantees.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20both%20Pakistan%20and%20India%2C%20Husain%20wrote%2C%20fear%20of%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20other%E2%80%99%20drove%20persecution%20and%20%E2%80%98robbed%20us%20of%20our%20humanity%E2%80%9D.%20The%20two%20could%20not%20settle%20disputes%20that%20were%20counterproductive%20for%20both%2C%20such%20as%20the%20troops-guzzling%2C%20financially%20exorbitant%20and%20ecologically%20damaging%20Siachen%20conflict.%20Had%20pre-partition%20economic%20interchange%2C%20freedom%20of%20movement%20and%20channels%20of%20communication%20been%20kept%20open%20between%20both%20countries%20post-partition%2C%20at%20least%20at%20the%20level%20of%20civil%20society%2C%20the%20two%20polities%20might%20have%20cultivated%20tolerance%2C%20without%20which%20%E2%80%9Ca%20constitution%20and%20all%20the%20trappings%20of%20democracy%20are%20worthless%E2%80%9D%20Husain%20wrote.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20seems%20odd%20to%20discuss%20a%20long-term%20settlement%20when%20the%20need%20of%20the%20hour%20is%20to%20wrest%20a%20ceasefire%20and%20provide%20humanitarian%20aid.%20But%20even%20if%20this%20horrifically%20brutal%20war%20ends%20soon%2C%20violence%20will%20recur%20as%20long%20as%20the%20occupation%20of%20Palestinian%20territories%20continues.%20As%20of%20now%2C%20all%20agree%20that%20neither%20a%20two-state%20nor%20a%20binational%20state%20agreement%20will%20transpire%20without%20coordinated%20and%20substantive%20international%20pressure%2C%20of%20which%20little%20has%20been%20seen.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EUnion%20external%20affairs%20minister%20S.%20Jaishankar%20reiterated%20his%20support%20for%20a%20two-state%20solution%20a%20few%20days%20ago.%20But%20the%20Modi%20administration%20is%20yet%20to%20join%20or%20contribute%20to%20the%20increasing%20number%20of%20countries%20demanding%20an%20immediate%20ceasefire%20and%20end%20to%20the%20occupation.%20That%20is%20in%20sharp%20contrast%20with%20not%20only%20most%20of%20the%20countries%20of%20%E2%80%98the%20Global%20South%E2%80%99%20but%20also%20the%20countries%20that%20underwent%20colonialism%20and%20oppose%20it%20now.%20Worse%2C%20it%20ignores%20the%20opinion%20of%20millions%20of%20Indian%20citizens.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ERadha%20Kumar%20is%20a%20writer%20and%20policy%20analyst.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702290629000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F03120804%2Fisrael-palestine.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fa-lasting-solution-for-israel-palestine-a-ceasefire-and-an-end-to-occupation%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Even%20if%20this%20horrifically%20brutal%20war%20ends%20soon%2C%20violence%20will%20recur%20as%20long%20as%20the%20occupation%20of%20Palestinian%20territories%20continues.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A3%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fa-lasting-solution-for-israel-palestine-a-ceasefire-and-an-end-to-occupation%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Revealed%3A%26nbsp%3BWhat%20we%20Googled%20most%20in%202023%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702290180000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fe3.365dm.com%2F23%2F12%2F768x432%2Fskynews-matthew-perry-barbie_6389750.jpg%3F20231211112158%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fgoogle-reveals-what-we-searched-for-the-most-in-2023-13028024%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Late%20actor%20Matthew%20Perry%2C%20the%20hunt%20for%20the%20missing%20Titanic%20submersible%2C%20and%20summer%20blockbuster%20Barbie%20were%20among%202023's%20most%20searched%20for%20topics%2C%20Google%20has%20revealed.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A7%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fgoogle-reveals-what-we-searched-for-the-most-in-2023-13028024%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews-sky-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fgoogle-reveals-what-we-searched-for-the-most-in-2023-13028024%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fgoogle-reveals-what-we-searched-for-the-most-in-2023-13028024%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22J%26amp%3BK%3A%20New%20Study%20Paints%20Grim%20Picture%20of%20Land%20Use%20Changes%20in%20Dachigam%20National%20Park%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F11151838%2FSarband-kashmir.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESrinagar%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Dachigam%20National%20Park%20(DNP)%2C%20a%20critical%20conservation%20reserve%20abutting%20one%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20four%20biodiversity%20hotspots%20in%20J%26amp%3BK%E2%80%99s%20Srinagar%2C%20has%20lost%20nearly%208%25%20forest%20cover%2C%20a%20new%20study%20has%20found.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFunded%20by%20the%20Government%20of%20India%20under%20the%20National%20Mission%20for%20Himalayan%20Studies%2C%20the%20study%20notes%20that%20Kashmir%E2%80%99s%20iconic%20Dal%20Lake%20in%20Srinagar%20city%20and%20other%20water%20bodies%20in%20the%20catchment%20area%20of%20DNP%20have%20nearly%20halved%20in%20size%2C%20from%2019.82%20sq%20km%20to%2010.62%20sq%20km.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20study%2C%20a%20model-based%20analysis%20of%20data%2C%20topographic%20maps%20and%20ground%20situation%20from%201965%20to%202020%2C%20warns%20that%20these%20changes%20are%20%E2%80%9Cindicative%20of%20fragmentation%20of%20natural%20habitats%E2%80%9D%20which%20will%20have%20a%20direct%20bearing%20on%20the%20park%E2%80%99s%20biodiversity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20peer-reviewed%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Flink.springer.com%2Farticle%2F10.1007%2Fs10661-023-11676-x%5C%22%3Estudy%3C%2Fa%3E%20appeared%20in%20the%20September%20issue%20of%20the%20journal%20%3Cem%3ESpringer%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20painting%20a%20grim%20picture%20of%20the%20land%20use%20changes%20in%20Dachigam%20which%20is%20located%20in%20the%20Zabarwan%20Range%20of%20the%20Himalayas%20and%20is%20home%20to%20the%20Kashmiri%20stag%20(Hangul)%20among%20other%20endemic%20and%20critically%20endangered%20species.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20the%20first%20time%20that%20an%20official%20study%20has%20concluded%20that%20not%20only%20the%20park%E2%80%99s%20forest%20cover%20but%20its%20%E2%80%9Ccore%20zone%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%93%20a%20protected%20area%20where%20human%20intervention%20is%20illegal%20%E2%80%93%20has%20also%20reduced%2C%20both%20outside%20the%20park%20and%20within%2C%20by%20more%20than%20a%20third.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENoting%20that%20the%20designation%20of%20DNP%20as%20a%20%E2%80%98protected%20area%E2%80%99%20hasn%E2%80%99t%20prevented%20habitat%20loss%20over%20the%20years%2C%20the%20study%20notes%20that%20the%20pastures%20and%20shrub-lands%20in%20the%20park%20will%20grow%20by%2048%25%20and%2037%25%20respectively%20while%20the%20forest%20cover%20is%20not%20expected%20to%20change%20much%20by%20the%20end%20of%20this%20century.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELocated%20some%2022%20km%20from%20Srinagar%20city%20centre%20Lal%20Chowk%2C%20Dachigam%20Park%20and%20its%20catchment%20areas%20are%20spread%20across%20337%20sq%20km%20in%20the%20eastern%20part%20of%20the%20Himalayas%2C%20serving%20not%20just%20as%20a%20habitat%20for%20some%20of%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20richest%20biodiversity%20but%20also%20as%20a%20quaint%20getaway%20for%20adventure%20lovers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDachigam%20used%20to%20be%20a%20residential%20area%20before%20World%20War%201.%20As%20wild%20animals%20were%20frequently%20sighted%20there%2C%20the%20then%20Dogra%20rulers%20of%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20vacated%20the%20inhabitants%20of%20ten%20villages%20there%20and%20converted%20it%20into%20a%20hunting%20reserve.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20reserve%2C%20which%20was%20declared%20a%20protected%20area%20in%201910%2C%20has%20thick%20coniferous%20forests%2C%20undulating%20pastures%20and%20gurgling%20water%20streams%20flowing%20down%20the%20mountains%20that%20not%20only%20sustain%20the%20Himalayan%20biodiversity%20and%20livelihoods%20of%20herding%20communities%20but%20also%20bring%20drinking%20water%20supply%20to%20Srinagar%20city%20from%20the%20high%20altitude%20alpine%20lakes%20of%20Lidder%20Valley.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F11151954%2Fhangul.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221149%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F11151954%2Fhangul.jpg%201149w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F11151954%2Fhangul-300x188.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F11151954%2Fhangul-1024x642.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-688645%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22720%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EA%20herd%20of%20Hangul%20(Kashmiri%20stag)%20in%20Dachigam.%20Photo%3A%20Tahirshawl%2FWikimedia%20Commons%2C%20CC%20BY-SA%204.0%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%2055-year%20study%2C%20which%20also%20analysed%20the%20United%20States%20Geological%20Survey%E2%80%99s%20(USGS)%20earth%20observation%20data%2C%20notes%20that%20the%20absence%20of%20a%20proper%20%E2%80%9Cland%20use%20policy%E2%80%9D%20in%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20accompanied%20by%20rapid%20and%20unplanned%20urbanisation%20raises%20troubling%20questions%20about%20the%20park%E2%80%99s%20future.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EExperts%20believe%20that%20the%20loss%20of%20habitat%20will%20increase%20the%20likelihood%20of%20man-animal%20conflicts%20and%20it%20may%20also%20have%20a%20direct%20bearing%20on%20the%20fate%20of%20the%20Kashmiri%20Hangul%2C%20which%20is%20accorded%20the%20highest%20protection%20under%20Schedule%20I%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20Wildlife%20Protection%20Act%2C%201972.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIrfan%20Rashid%2C%20assistant%20professor%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Kashmir%E2%80%99s%20Geoinformatics%20Department%2C%20said%20that%20the%20degradation%20of%20land%20cover%20can%20have%20serious%20implications%20not%20just%20for%20DNP%2C%20which%20was%20declared%20a%20national%20park%20in%201981%2C%20but%20also%20for%20Dal%20Lake%2C%20which%20is%20located%20downstream%20of%20the%20park.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAny%20reduction%20in%20green%20cover%20would%20increase%20the%20silt%20load%20in%20the%20stream%20that%20ultimately%20pours%20out%20into%20Dal%20lake.%20This%20would%20lead%20to%20enrichment%20of%20Nitrogen%20and%20Phosphorus%20in%20lake%E2%80%99s%20waters%2C%20a%20process%20called%20eutrophication%2C%20that%20has%20immense%20implications%20for%20lake%20water%20quality%2C%20biota%20and%20aesthetics%2C%E2%80%9D%20Rashid%2C%20one%20of%20the%20study%E2%80%99s%20authors%2C%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20study%20comes%20out%20at%20a%20time%20when%20the%20Union%20Ministry%20of%20Environment%2C%20Forest%20and%20Climate%20Change%20told%20parliament%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pib.gov.in%2FPressReleseDetailm.aspx%3FPRID%3D1906388%5C%22%3EMarch%20this%20year%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20forest%20cover%20in%20J%26amp%3BK%20increased%20marginally%20by%200.14%25%20since%202019.%20According%20to%20official%20data%2C%2039.15%25%20of%20J%26amp%3BK%20is%20forest%20area%2C%20spanning%2021%2C387%20sq%20km.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnsustainable%20development%20and%20unregulated%20human%20footprint%20have%20accelerated%20climate%20change%20which%20is%20feared%20to%20cause%20irreversible%20damage%20to%20the%20mountain%20ecosystem%20in%20the%20Kashmir%20Himalayas.%20Experts%20believe%20that%20the%20diminishing%20size%20of%20Dachigam%20will%20shrink%20its%20natural%20habitats.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20most%20serious%20concern%20is%20the%20increase%20in%20the%20incidence%20of%20human-wildlife%20conflicts%20which%20are%20becoming%20more%20frequent%20all%20across%20Kashmir%20since%20a%20lot%20of%20infrastructure%20development%20(roads%2C%20buildings)%20is%20happening%20in%20otherwise%20natural%20forested%20landscapes.%20Other%20issues%20could%20be%20increased%20nutrient%20enrichment%20of%20waters%20from%20domestic%20sewage%2C%E2%80%9D%20Rashid%20told%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EApproached%20for%20comment%2C%20a%20senior%20officer%20in%20the%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20administration%20referred%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20to%20the%20Regional%20Wildlife%20Warden%2C%20Kashmir%2C%20Rashid%20Yahya%20Naqash%2C%20who%20sought%20to%20question%20the%20methodology%20used%20in%20the%20study%20while%20also%20rejecting%20the%20findings.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThere%20has%20been%20no%20negative%20change%20in%20Dachigam.%20The%20park%20is%20healthy%20and%20there%20are%20several%20studies%20which%20have%20found%20that%20the%20park%E2%80%99s%20forest%20cover%20has%20increased%20over%20the%20years%2C%E2%80%9D%20Yahya%20said%2C%20referring%20to%20a%2030-year%20study%20from%201989%20to%202019%20which%20suggests%20that%20the%20park%E2%80%99s%20forest%20cover%20has%20increased%20by%20between%2014.91%25%20and%2016.96%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20pointed%20out%20to%20him%20that%20the%20latest%20study%20was%20based%20on%20scientific%20data%20and%20ground%20validation%2C%20and%20that%20officials%20of%20the%20Wildlife%20Department%20and%20the%20University%20of%20Kashmir%20were%20part%20of%20the%20study%2C%20Naqash%20sought%20more%20time%20before%20responding.%20Later%2C%20both%20the%20officials%20didn%E2%80%99t%20answer%20calls.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20study%2C%20the%20park%20has%20lost%20six%20sq%20km%20or%20close%20to%208%25%20of%20its%20forest%20cover%20in%2055%20years%20while%20the%20%E2%80%98exposed%20rock%E2%80%99%20area%20reduced%20by%204.26%20sq%20km%20(13%25)%20from%2027.28%20sq%20km%20to%2023.02%20sq%20km.%20However%2C%20the%20study%20notes%20that%20the%20reduction%20in%20forest%20cover%20has%20seen%20an%20increase%20in%20the%20park%E2%80%99s%20shrublands%20which%20grew%20by%207.3%20sq%20km%20(56.28%25)%20while%20the%20park%E2%80%99s%20alpine%20pasture%20increased%20by%208.02%20sq%20km%20(31.89%25).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20study%20has%20also%20found%20that%20the%20land%20around%20the%20park%20under%20agriculture%20shrank%20by%2075.16%25%20(from%2040.02%20sq%20km%20in%201965%20to%20merely%209.94%20sq%20km%20in%202020)%20and%20alpine%20pasture%20nearly%20halved%20by%2046.68%25%20or%205.28%20sq%20km.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnsurprisingly%2C%20the%20study%20notes%20that%20there%20has%20been%20a%20three-fold%20increase%20(326%25)%20or%2024.66%20sq%20km%20expansion%20of%20the%20built-up%20area%20around%20the%20park%2C%20which%20includes%20orchards%2C%20and%20residential%20and%20commercial%20areas%2C%20while%20aquatic%20vegetation%20outside%20the%20park%20expanded%20by%20174%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20study%20points%20out%20that%20the%20water-intensive%20croplands%20around%20DNP%20shrunk%20by%2075%25%20in%20the%2055-year%20study%20period%20and%20they%20have%20been%20replaced%20either%20by%20built-up%20areas%20or%20apple%20orchards%2C%20a%20trend%20which%20is%20projected%20to%20accelerate%20in%20coming%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702288829000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F11151838%2FSarband-kashmir.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fjk-dachigam-national-park-grim-picture-forest-cover%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20park%2C%20located%20near%20Srinagar%2C%20lost%208%25%20of%20its%20forest%20cover%20in%2055%20years%20while%20the%20%E2%80%98exposed%20rock%E2%80%99%20area%20reduced%20by%2013%25.%20There%20was%20an%20increase%20in%20the%20park%E2%80%99s%20shrublands%20and%20alpine%20pastures.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A4%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fjk-dachigam-national-park-grim-picture-forest-cover%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Two%20shot%20dead%20in%20Swiss%20town%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702287480000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fe3.365dm.com%2F23%2F12%2F768x432%2Fskynews-police-scene-switzerland_6389739.jpg%3F20231211110941%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fsion-two-shot-dead-in-swiss-town-13027995%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Two%20people%20have%20been%20killed%20and%20a%20third%20injured%20in%20a%20shooting%20in%20a%20southern%20Swiss%20town%2C%20police%20have%20said.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A113%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fsion-two-shot-dead-in-swiss-town-13027995%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews-sky-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fsion-two-shot-dead-in-swiss-town-13027995%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fsion-two-shot-dead-in-swiss-town-13027995%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Four%20Important%20Takeaways%20From%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20Ruling%20on%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F04%2F07121155%2FSupreme_Court_of_India_inside_bulidings_02.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20Supreme%20Court%20on%20Monday%2C%20December%2011%2C%20has%20ruled%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fsupreme-court-kashmir-article-370-verdict%5C%22%3Euphold%20the%20reading%20down%20of%20Article%20370%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20a%20few%20important%20implications%20on%20matters%20beyond%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20and%20Ladakh%20flowing%20from%20these%20judgments%20and%20pronouncements%20from%20a%20five-judge%20bench%20that%20unanimously%20upheld%20all%20government%20moves%20on%20August%205%2C%202019%20and%20other%20acts%20that%20followed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E1.%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%20D.Y.%20Chandrachud%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livelaw.in%2Ftop-stories%2Farticle-370-supreme-court-abrogation-of-special-status-of-jammu-and-kashmir-244198%3Finfinitescroll%3D1%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20not%20every%20decision%20by%20the%20Union%20government%20can%20be%20challenged%3A%20%E2%80%9CEvery%20decision%20taken%20by%20Union%20on%20behalf%20of%20State%20during%20Presidential%20rule%20not%20open%20to%20challenge%E2%80%A6this%20will%20lead%20to%20the%20administration%20of%20state%20to%20a%20standstill.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%2C%20coming%20from%20the%20apex%2C%20constitutional%20court%20of%20India%2C%20has%20implications%2C%20especially%20if%20said%20as%20part%20of%20an%20order%20and%20while%20there%20is%20an%20executive%20with%20a%20%E2%80%98strong%E2%80%99%20majority%20in%20place.%20It%20calls%20to%20question%20the%20power%20of%20every%20citizen%2C%20in%20principle%2C%20expecting%20the%20courts%20to%20be%20able%20to%20act%20as%20a%20check%20on%20the%20government%20of%20the%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22As%20Supreme%20Court%20Rules%20on%20Article%20370%20in%20J%26amp%3BK%2C%20Here%E2%80%99s%20Why%20History%2C%20Legal%20Context%20Matters%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhistory%2Farticle-370-understanding-the-history-legal-contexts-and-why-it-matters%5C%22%3EAs%20Supreme%20Court%20Rules%20on%20Article%20370%20in%20J%26amp%3BK%2C%20Here%E2%80%99s%20Why%20History%2C%20Legal%20Context%20Matters%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E2.%20The%20court%20has%20held%20that%20it%20is%20not%20going%20into%20the%20question%20of%20whether%20parliament%20can%20convert%20a%20state%20into%20a%20union%20territory%2C%20and%20left%20this%20open.%20The%20reorganisation%20of%20Ladakh%20as%20a%20union%20territory%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livelaw.in%2Ftop-stories%2Farticle-370-supreme-court-abrogation-of-special-status-of-jammu-and-kashmir-244198%3Finfinitescroll%3D1%5C%22%3Ewas%20upheld%20as%20Article%203%20allowed%20a%20portion%20of%20the%20state%20to%20be%20made%20as%20UT.%3C%2Fa%3E%20The%20court%20said%20that%20it%20is%20doing%20so%20because%20the%20solicitor%20general%20has%20promised%20that%20statehood%20will%20be%20restored.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20key%20question%20was%20if%20the%20statehood%20of%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20can%20be%20done%20away%20with%2C%20with%20no%20state%20assembly%20being%20in%20place%20and%20the%20Union%20government%20arrogating%20to%20parliament%20the%20powers%20to%20decide%20on%20the%20region%E2%80%99s%20behalf%20and%20stripping%20down%20its%20status.%20This%20was%20a%20first%20in%20India%20and%20the%20apex%20court%20not%20going%20into%20it%20has%20implications%20on%20future%20attempts%20by%20this%20government%20or%20another%20in%20its%20place%2C%20embarking%20on%20drives%20to%20make%20fundamental%20changes%20to%20India%E2%80%99s%20federal%20structure%2C%20of%20which%20states%20are%20the%20central%20building%20blocks.%20Does%20this%20make%20Article%201%20of%20the%20Constitution%2C%20that%20%E2%80%9CIndia%20is%20a%20union%20of%20states%E2%80%9D%2C%20up%20for%20challenge%20too%2C%20or%20render%20it%20an%20%E2%80%9Copen%E2%80%9D%20proposition%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E3.%20The%20court%20directed%20the%20Election%20Commission%20of%20India%20to%20hold%20elections%20%E2%80%9Cby%20September%2030%2C%202024%E2%80%9D%2C%20which%20was%20interesting%20as%20it%20effectively%20meant%20directing%20an%20autonomous%20body%20(the%20Election%20Commission)%20which%20is%20meant%20to%20decide%20on%20when%20to%20hold%20polls%20independently.%20The%20call%20for%20elections%20was%20not%20a%20prayer%20in%20any%20of%20the%20petitions.%20In%20effect%2C%20it%20allows%20the%20postponing%20of%20polls%20to%20beyond%20even%20the%20time%20when%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20country%20is%20set%20to%20go%20to%20polls%20in%20a%20general%20election%20by%20spring%20next%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJammu%20and%20Kashmir%20has%20not%20seen%20assembly%20elections%20in%20nearly%20a%20decade%3B%20the%20last%20time%20polls%20were%20held%20was%20in%20five%20phases%20between%20November-December%202014.%20It%20is%20also%20a%20setback%20to%20the%20Union%20government%E2%80%99s%20current%20favourite%20theme%20of%20%E2%80%98One%20Nation%20One%20Election%E2%80%99%2C%20or%20simultaneous%20polls%20in%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Ffull-text-karan-thapar-tarunabh-khaitan-bjp-narendra-modi-hindu-rashtra%5C%22%3EAutocrats%20Have%20Learnt%20To%20Push%20Their%20Agenda%20While%20Retaining%20Paraphernalia%20of%20Democracy%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E4.%20Justice%20Sanjay%20Kishen%20Kaul%20in%20his%20epilogue%20has%20mooted%20a%20%E2%80%98truth%20and%20reconciliation%20committee%E2%80%99%20for%20the%20union%20territory%2C%20a%20time-bound%20exercise%20to%20investigate%20and%20report%20on%20the%20violations%20of%20human%20rights%20by%20both%20State%20and%20non-state%20actors%20at%20least%20since%20the%201980s%20and%20recommend%20measures%20for%20reconciliation.%20Justice%20Kaul%20mentioned%20the%20South%20African%20commission%20for%20truth%20and%20reconciliation%20as%20a%20model%20and%20said%20it%20should%20be%20done%20to%20heal%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livelaw.in%2Fbuzz%2Farticle-370-case-judgment-live-updates-from-supreme-court-on-jammu-kashmir-special-status-25656%5C%22%3E%E2%80%9Cinter-generational%20trauma%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9Cbefore%20memory%20escapes%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECould%20the%20rest%20of%20India%20look%20upon%20this%20as%20a%20model%20on%20key%20questions%20and%20divides%20which%20are%20wide%20open%20at%20a%20time%20of%20extreme%20polarisation%3F%20On%20caste%20atrocities%20and%20on%20restoring%20the%20idea%20of%20fraternity%3F%20The%20idea%20of%20having%20such%20commissions%20can%20sometimes%20be%20controversial%20and%20rake%20up%20wounds%20of%20the%20past%20at%20a%20time%20of%20a%20majoritarian%20sway%20in%20the%20polity%2C%20but%20this%20could%20also%20offer%20a%20way%20out%20of%20some%20intractable%20problems%20and%20help%20acknowledge%20societal%20divides.%20If%20nothing%20else%2C%20it%20may%20help%20frame%20the%20problem%20and%20underline%20a%20commitment%20to%20build%20bridges%20in%20a%20plural%20society.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702285403000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F04%2F07121155%2FSupreme_Court_of_India_inside_bulidings_02.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Ffour-important-takeaways-from-the-supreme-court-ruling-on-jammu-and-kashmir%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Many%20pronouncements%20and%20utterances%20today%20will%20have%20serious%20implications%20on%20India%E2%80%99s%20two%20northern-most%20union%20territories%2C%20but%20also%20for%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20country.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A18%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Ffour-important-takeaways-from-the-supreme-court-ruling-on-jammu-and-kashmir%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22'Time%20for%20Action%20to%20Prevent%20Genocide%20Is%20Now'%3A%20Holocaust%20Scholars%20on%20Israel's%20Attacks%20on%20Gaza%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F16120732%2Fimage1170x530cropped-5.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Rhetoric%20in%20Israel%20surrounding%20the%20war%20in%20Gaza%20portends%20an%20escalation%20of%20violence%20against%20Palestinians%2C%20a%20group%20of%2056%20Holocaust%20and%20genocide%20studies%20scholars%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcontendingmodernities.nd.edu%2Fglobal-currents%2Fstatement-of-scholars-7-october%2F%5C%22%3Ehave%20warned%20in%20an%20open%20letter%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThey%20said%20there%20is%20a%20risk%20of%20genocide%20against%20Palestinians%20and%20called%20for%20concerted%20action%20to%20prevent%20it%2C%20including%20by%20working%20to%20end%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20military%20offensive%20into%20Gaza%20and%20to%20investigate%20acts%20of%20mass%20violence%20perpetrated%20since%20October%207%20by%20Israelis%20or%20Palestinians.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%2C%20scholars%20of%20the%20Holocaust%2C%20genocide%2C%20and%20mass%20violence%2C%20feel%20compelled%20to%20warn%20of%20the%20danger%20of%20genocide%20in%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20attack%20on%20Gaza%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20scholars%20opened%20their%20letter%20by%20saying.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThey%20condemned%20both%20Hamas%E2%80%99s%20October%207%20attack%20on%20Israel%20as%20well%20as%20the%20ongoing%20Israeli%20military%20operation%20in%20Gaza%2C%20and%20said%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.timesofisrael.com%2Fliveblog-october-7-2023%2F%5C%22%3EHamas%E2%80%99%20October%207%20attack%3C%2Fa%3E%20should%20be%20placed%20in%20the%20context%20of%20Israeli%20military%20and%20political%20decisions%20since%20the%201960s.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CExplaining%20is%20not%20justifying%2C%20and%20this%20context%20in%20no%20way%20excuses%20the%20targeting%20of%20Israeli%20civilians%20and%20migrant%20workers%20by%20Palestinians%20on%20October%207%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20scholars%20clarified.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETheir%20letter%20gives%20examples%20of%20inflammatory%20or%20dehumanising%20language%20used%20in%20Israel%20against%20Gazans%20as%20a%20whole%2C%20including%20those%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FYehudaShaul%2Fstatus%2F1714301958607999071%5C%22%3Eallegedly%20used%20by%20Israeli%20journalists%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20by%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.timesofisrael.com%2Fliveblog_entry%2Fcogat-chief-addresses-gazans-you-wanted-hell-you-will-get-hell%2F%5C%22%3EIsraeli%20army%20major%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20also%20notes%20that%20the%20use%20of%20such%20language%20puts%20Palestinians%20outside%20Gaza%2C%20such%20as%20those%20living%20in%20the%20West%20Bank%20or%20those%20who%20were%20citizens%20of%20Israel%2C%20in%20danger%20as%20well.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EComments%20made%20by%20an%20Israeli%20parliamentarian%20from%20the%20Israeli%20prime%20minister%E2%80%99s%20Likud%20party%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FArielKallner%2Fstatus%2F1710769363119141268%5C%22%3Eseemingly%20seeking%20a%20second%C2%A0%3Cem%3ENakba%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20also%20mentioned%20in%20the%20letter.%20%3Cem%3ENakba%3C%2Fem%3E%20is%20an%20Arabic%20word%20used%20to%20refer%20to%20the%20dispossession%20of%20Palestinians%20when%20Israel%20was%20created.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20know%20that%20genocide%20is%20a%20process%2C%20and%20we%20recognise%20that%20the%20stage%20is%20thus%20set%20for%20violence%20%3Cem%3Emore%3C%2Fem%3E%20severe%20than%20the%20Nakba%20and%20not%20spatially%20limited%20to%20Gaza%2C%20%5Bemphasis%20retained%5D%E2%80%9D%20the%20scholars%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEnding%20their%20letter%20by%20urging%20immediate%20and%20concerted%20action%20to%20prevent%20a%20genocide%2C%20the%20scholars%20said%20that%20governments%20must%20take%20six%20steps%20to%20achieve%20this.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20included%20imposing%20an%20arms%20embargo%20on%20Israel%2C%20%E2%80%9Cpressuring%20the%20Israeli%20government%20to%20stop%20immediately%E2%80%9D%20the%20settler%20violence%20in%20the%20West%20Bank%2C%20issuing%20arrest%20warrants%20against%20perpetrators%20of%20mass%20violence%20both%20Palestinian%20and%20Israeli%2C%20and%20initiating%20a%20%E2%80%9Cpolitical%20process%20in%20Israel%20and%20Palestine%20based%20on%20a%20truthful%20reckoning%20with%20Israeli%20mass%20violence%20against%20Palestinians%20since%20the%201948%20Nakba.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThey%20also%20urged%20Holocaust%20and%20genocide%20studies%20scholars%20to%20%E2%80%9Ctake%20a%20clear%20stance%20against%20Israeli%20mass%20violence%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Ciframe%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22allowfullscreen%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2FavT8I2UADKA%3Fsi%3DEwwG9KOqRDZa1AFi%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22560%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22YouTube%20video%20player%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22315%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20letter%20is%20reproduced%20in%20full%20below.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A7%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EStatement%20of%20Scholars%20in%20Holocaust%20and%20Genocide%20Studies%20on%20Mass%20Violence%20in%20Israel%20and%20Palestine%20since%207%20October%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDecember%209%2C%202023%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWe%2C%20scholars%20of%20the%20Holocaust%2C%20genocide%2C%20and%20mass%20violence%2C%20feel%20compelled%20to%20warn%20of%20the%20danger%20of%20genocide%20in%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20attack%20on%20Gaza.%20We%20also%20note%20that%2C%20should%20the%20Israeli%20attack%20continue%20and%20escalate%2C%20Palestinians%20under%20Israeli%20military%20occupation%20in%20the%20West%20Bank%20and%20East%20Jerusalem%20and%20Palestinian%20citizens%20of%20Israel%20face%20grave%20danger%20as%20well.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWe%20are%20deeply%20saddened%20and%20concerned%20by%20the%20mass%20murder%20of%20over%201%2C200%20Israelis%20and%20migrant%20workers%20by%20Hamas%2C%20the%20Islamic%20Jihad%2C%20and%20others%20on%207%20October%2C%20with%20more%20than%20830%20civilians%20among%20them.%20We%20also%20note%20the%20evidence%20of%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22external%20noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.phr.org.il%2Fen%2Fgender-based-violence-eng%2F%5C%22%20data-wpel-link%3D%5C%22external%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egender-based%20and%20sexual%20violence%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0during%20the%20attack%2C%20the%20wounding%20of%20thousands%20of%20Israelis%2C%20the%20destruction%20of%20Israeli%20kibbutzim%20and%20towns%2C%20and%20the%20abduction%20of%20more%20than%20240%20hostages%20into%20the%20Gaza%20Strip.%20These%20acts%20constitute%20war%20crimes%20and%20crimes%20against%20humanity.%20We%20recognize%20that%20violence%20in%20Israel%20and%20Palestine%20did%20not%20begin%20on%207%20October.%20If%20we%20are%20to%20try%20to%20understand%20the%20mass%20murder%20of%207%20October%2C%20we%20should%20place%20it%20within%20the%20context%20of%20Israeli%20settler%20colonialism%2C%20Israeli%20military%20occupation%20violence%20against%20Palestinians%20since%201967%2C%20the%20sixteen-year%20siege%20on%20the%20Gaza%20Strip%20since%202007%2C%20and%20the%20rise%20to%20power%20in%20Israel%20in%20the%20last%20year%20of%20a%20government%20made%20up%20of%20politicians%20who%20speak%20proudly%20about%20Jewish%20supremacy%20and%20exclusionary%20nationalism.%20Explaining%20is%20not%20justifying%2C%20and%20this%20context%20in%20no%20way%20excuses%20the%20targeting%20of%20Israeli%20civilians%20and%20migrant%20workers%20by%20Palestinians%20on%207%20October.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWe%20are%20also%20deeply%20saddened%20and%20concerned%20by%20the%20Israeli%20attack%20on%20Gaza%20in%20response%20to%20the%20Hamas%20attack.%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20assault%20has%20caused%20death%20and%20destruction%20on%20an%20unprecedented%20level%2C%20according%20to%20a%20New%20York%20Times%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22external%20noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2023%2F11%2F25%2Fworld%2Fmiddleeast%2Fisrael-gaza-deat